INFO 05-05 17:10:59 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-24e19a9a731d43a1885ec1b89654b455-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of earthquakes for a high school student preparing for a class discussion. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. Also include a discussion of how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to earthquakes. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. A useful answer should cover a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to earthquakes. To make the response more complete, include a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to earthquakes. The explanation should not ignore the short-term effects people notice first in relation to earthquakes.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=128, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 8437, 339, 6926, 363, 263, 1880, 3762, 8368, 10223, 292, 363, 263, 770, 10679, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 3115, 3160, 263, 10679, 310, 920, 304, 20820, 17924, 1136, 8841, 515, 1722, 27836, 297, 8220, 304, 8437, 339, 6926, 29889, 8984, 714, 738, 3619, 3984, 535, 1441, 29879, 393, 1033, 3275, 304, 6460, 1602, 12112, 29889, 319, 5407, 1234, 881, 4612, 263, 1206, 988, 1781, 7609, 1080, 508, 7738, 8062, 2582, 297, 8220, 304, 8437, 339, 6926, 29889, 1763, 1207, 278, 2933, 901, 4866, 29892, 3160, 263, 1855, 29899, 11526, 3483, 6933, 393, 947, 451, 288, 874, 13699, 1598, 278, 22