INFO 05-05 17:11:32 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-ccb4507e412e44d0a261875823416964-0: prompt: 'I need a well-organized answer about linguistics. Assume the reader is a museum educator designing an accessible exhibit, and focus on clarity, examples, tradeoffs, and common misunderstandings. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to linguistics. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. Where appropriate, include how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to linguistics. As part of the explanation, address how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to linguistics.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=128, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 21110, 6765, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 19133, 6320, 1061, 2874, 292, 385, 15579, 10371, 277, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 920, 304, 5649, 278, 11261, 1728, 337, 5890, 373, 432, 1191, 265, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 8561, 278, 2933, 5407, 363, 4856, 1058, 4225, 1716, 3239, 7134, 322, 15031, 24284, 29889, 6804, 8210, 29892, 3160, 920, 25812, 881, 367, 16459, 746, 10757, 338, 28907, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 1094, 760, 310, 278, 8252, 29892, 3211, 920, 278, 11261, 1033, 6602, 2305, 17587, 8679, 373, 5046, 29892, 17869, 29892, 4423, 29892, 470, 9