INFO 05-05 17:11:44 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-2f5499e412c6405c865aa6e8ae61bfff-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of epidemiology for a parent trying to explain the idea to a teenager. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. Please also examine how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to epidemiology. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. A balanced response should mention the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to epidemiology. For practical context, discuss what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to epidemiology. To avoid oversimplifying, include what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to epidemiology.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=128, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 9358, 680, 2460, 3002, 363, 263, 3847, 1811, 304, 5649, 278, 2969, 304, 263, 734, 264, 1875, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 3529, 884, 25917, 920, 848, 11029, 508, 8267, 278, 12536, 3097, 310, 21204, 1080, 297, 8220, 304, 9358, 680, 2460, 3002, 29889, 4803, 6455, 16112, 322, 5649, 2020, 1269, 1342, 11286, 278, 2545, 1664, 1298, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 278, 16905, 11938, 393, 1207, 2560, 6851, 5189, 297, 8220, 304, 9358, 680, 2460, 3002, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 825, 5155, 263, 18109, 415, 936, 20026, 723, 3117, 2244, 297, 8220