INFO 05-05 17:11:46 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-d71d73b5043b44a6a96633db75ef25b5-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand history of medicine from the perspective of a community organizer preparing a public workshop. Please teach the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. A balanced response should mention one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to history of medicine. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. To avoid oversimplifying, include the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to history of medicine. When developing the answer, connect this to a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to history of medicine.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=128, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 4955, 310, 26602, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 7881, 2894, 3950, 10223, 292, 263, 970, 664, 19032, 29889, 3529, 6860, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 697, 18387, 1342, 393, 3732, 278, 6964, 6775, 304, 2274, 297, 8220, 304, 4955, 310, 26602, 29889, 12027, 7420, 278, 4328, 1546, 19869, 29892, 3269, 362, 29892, 322, 15590, 27262, 746, 8018, 29889, 1763, 4772, 288, 874, 13699, 9215, 29892, 3160, 278, 4328, 1546, 5557, 291, 29892, 28206, 29892, 322, 1380, 335, 362, 16650, 583, 297, 8220, 304, 4955, 310, 26602, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 263, 1855, 29899, 11526