INFO 05-05 17:12:28 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-f721feefd18a4af5a978acfbfbfff6cc-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of behavioral economics for a curious adult with no technical background. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. When developing the answer, connect this to the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to behavioral economics. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. The response should make room for how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to behavioral economics. Where appropriate, include the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to behavioral economics.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=128, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 6030, 284, 7766, 1199, 363, 263, 12758, 16157, 411, 694, 16905, 3239, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 278, 3957, 1546, 5375, 19995, 322, 7200, 1788, 29899, 5563, 714, 26807, 297, 8220, 304, 6030, 284, 7766, 1199, 29889, 4803, 6455, 515, 901, 1135, 697, 3030, 565, 393, 6911, 1510, 2020, 278, 2228, 338, 12092, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 1207, 5716, 363, 920, 304, 1207, 278, 8252, 5407, 304, 4856, 1058, 1818, 1207, 263, 10608, 297, 8220, 304, 6030, 284, 7766, 1199, 29889, 6804, 8210, 29892, 3160, 278, 15839, 2693, 1860, 393, 1754, 278, 2228