INFO 05-05 17:15:03 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-86246c75ab87445da898cd14fec64a44-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand ocean ecosystems from the perspective of a curious adult with no technical background. Please clarify the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Please also examine why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to ocean ecosystems. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. A balanced response should mention what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to ocean ecosystems. For practical context, discuss how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to ocean ecosystems. To avoid oversimplifying, include a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to ocean ecosystems. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. A reader would also benefit from understanding the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to ocean ecosystems. The response should make room for the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to ocean ecosystems. Where appropriate, include how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to ocean ecosystems. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. Also include a discussion of the most realistic solutions available today in relation to ocean ecosystems. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=256, min_tokens=0, log