INFO 05-05 17:16:19 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-1d40dd02d33440e2a92b57fb4eafe573-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand linguistics from the perspective of a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions. Please evaluate the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Please also examine why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to linguistics. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. A balanced response should mention how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to linguistics. For practical context, discuss the most realistic solutions available today in relation to linguistics. To avoid oversimplifying, include a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to linguistics. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. A reader would also benefit from understanding an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to linguistics. The response should make room for ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to linguistics. Where appropriate, include how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to linguistics. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. Also include a discussion of the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to linguistics. In addition, consider how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to linguistics.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=256, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=Tr