INFO 05-05 17:17:36 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-c18933e219e14e4187eedb729157f7c7-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand language learning from the perspective of a policymaker looking for practical implications rather than slogans. Please teach the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Another important angle is how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to language learning. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. For practical context, discuss a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to language learning. To avoid oversimplifying, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to language learning. When developing the answer, connect this to the most realistic solutions available today in relation to language learning. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. The response should make room for how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to language learning. Where appropriate, include the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to language learning. As part of the explanation, address the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to language learning. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. In addition, consider a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to language learning. A useful answer should cover how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to language learning. To make the response more complete, include the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to language learning. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. Please also examine how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to language learning. Another important angle is ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to language learning. A balanced response should mention the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to language learning. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. To avoid oversimplifying, include what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to language learning. When developing the answer, connect this to how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to language learning. A reader would also benefit from understanding a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to language learning. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. Where appropriate, include a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to language learning. As part of the explanation, address an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to language learning. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 4086, 6509, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 13665, 962, 5790, 3063, 363, 15031, 2411, 5795, 3265, 1135, 269, 1188, 550, 29889, 3529, 6860, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 920, 25812, 881, 367, 16459, 746, 10757, 338, 28907, 297, 8220, 304, 4086, 6509, 29889, 1938, 451, 5251