INFO 05-05 17:17:46 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-381af84e5ecf4deb9aa17be84f1b4984-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about ancient civilizations for a parent trying to explain the idea to a teenager. Please summarize the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. For practical context, discuss the short-term effects people notice first in relation to ancient civilizations. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. When developing the answer, connect this to how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to ancient civilizations. A reader would also benefit from understanding what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to ancient civilizations. The response should make room for a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to ancient civilizations. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. As part of the explanation, address the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to ancient civilizations. Also include a discussion of an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to ancient civilizations. In addition, consider the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to ancient civilizations. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. To make the response more complete, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to ancient civilizations. The explanation should not ignore what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to ancient civilizations. Please also examine the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to ancient civilizations. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. A balanced response should mention an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to ancient civilizations. For practical context, discuss why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to ancient civilizations. To avoid oversimplifying, include the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to ancient civilizations. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to ancient civilizations. The response should make room for how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to ancient civilizations. Where appropriate, include the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to ancient civilizations. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. Also include a discussion of how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to ancient civilizations. Please emphasize clarity, accuracy, and balanced reasoning throughout the response.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 1954, 22094, 366, 526, 10223, 292, 263, 2821, 28976, 1234, 1048, 12297, 7631, 17063, 363, 263, 3847, 1811, 304, 5649, 278, 2969, 304, 263, 734, 264, 1875, 29889, 3529, 19138, 675, 278, 6964, 29892, 2020, 372, 13750, 29892, 322, 920, 2305, 881, 1348, 1048, 967, 150