INFO 05-05 17:17:51 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-3cabeb9a25014585950156f15e03322f-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of democracy for a high school student preparing for a class discussion. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. To avoid oversimplifying, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to democracy. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to democracy. The response should make room for what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to democracy. Where appropriate, include how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to democracy. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. Also include a discussion of the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to democracy. In addition, consider the most realistic solutions available today in relation to democracy. A useful answer should cover how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to democracy. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. The explanation should not ignore the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to democracy. Please also examine the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to democracy. Another important angle is the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to democracy. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. For practical context, discuss how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to democracy. To avoid oversimplifying, include a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to democracy. When developing the answer, connect this to how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to democracy. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. The response should make room for a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to democracy. Where appropriate, include one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to democracy. As part of the explanation, address the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to democracy. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. In addition, consider why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to democracy. A useful answer should cover which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to democracy. To make the response more complete, include how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to democracy. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 1261, 25804, 363, 263, 1880, 3762, 8368, 10223, 292, 363, 263, 770, 10679, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 1763, 4772, 288, 874, 13699, 9215, 29892, 3160, 607, 4958, 881, 367, 3342, 1434, 5353, 292, 278, 4902