INFO 05-05 17:17:56 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-3f6ab34c8d4b4d03bfc1f626d31ab688-0: prompt: 'I need a well-organized answer about wildlife conservation. Assume the reader is a community organizer preparing a public workshop, and focus on clarity, examples, tradeoffs, and common misunderstandings. When developing the answer, connect this to the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to wildlife conservation. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. The response should make room for which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to wildlife conservation. Where appropriate, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to wildlife conservation. As part of the explanation, address how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to wildlife conservation. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. In addition, consider the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to wildlife conservation. A useful answer should cover the main causes that created the current situation in relation to wildlife conservation. To make the response more complete, include how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to wildlife conservation. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. Please also examine how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to wildlife conservation. Another important angle is what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to wildlife conservation. A balanced response should mention what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to wildlife conservation. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. To avoid oversimplifying, include one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to wildlife conservation. When developing the answer, connect this to which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to wildlife conservation. A reader would also benefit from understanding the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to wildlife conservation. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. Where appropriate, include how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to wildlife conservation. As part of the explanation, address a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to wildlife conservation. Also include a discussion of a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to wildlife conservation. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. A useful answer should cover the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to wildlife conservation. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 8775, 19264, 24201, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 7881, 2894, 3950, 10223, 292, 263, 970, 664, 19032, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 451