INFO 05-05 17:18:01 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-b7593d72dcb84c61917bea6c6fa11e53-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand neuroscience from the perspective of a museum educator designing an accessible exhibit. Please analyze the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. A reader would also benefit from understanding the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to neuroscience. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. Where appropriate, include the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to neuroscience. As part of the explanation, address what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to neuroscience. Also include a discussion of ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to neuroscience. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. A useful answer should cover the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to neuroscience. To make the response more complete, include one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to neuroscience. The explanation should not ignore the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to neuroscience. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. Another important angle is how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to neuroscience. A balanced response should mention the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to neuroscience. For practical context, discuss the main causes that created the current situation in relation to neuroscience. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. When developing the answer, connect this to how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to neuroscience. A reader would also benefit from understanding how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to neuroscience. The response should make room for an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to neuroscience. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. As part of the explanation, address a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to neuroscience. Also include a discussion of how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to neuroscience. In addition, consider what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to neuroscience. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. To make the response more complete, include the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to neuroscience. The explanation should not ignore why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to neuroscience. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 17167, 1883, 15277, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 19133, 6320, 1061, 2874, 292, 385, 15579, 10371, 277, 29889, 3529, 27599, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 278, 4328, 1546, 5557, 291, 29892, 28206, 29892, 322, 1380, 335, 362,