INFO 05-05 17:18:06 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-2dc9ebd66fc344a4965fe1a3fe551872-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about green chemistry for a university student writing an introductory essay. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. The response should make room for how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to green chemistry. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. As part of the explanation, address how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to green chemistry. Also include a discussion of what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to green chemistry. In addition, consider how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to green chemistry. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. To make the response more complete, include the short-term effects people notice first in relation to green chemistry. The explanation should not ignore an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to green chemistry. Please also examine ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to green chemistry. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. A balanced response should mention one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to green chemistry. For practical context, discuss the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to green chemistry. To avoid oversimplifying, include the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to green chemistry. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. A reader would also benefit from understanding the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to green chemistry. The response should make room for the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to green chemistry. Where appropriate, include what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to green chemistry. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. Also include a discussion of how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to green chemistry. In addition, consider how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to green chemistry. A useful answer should cover the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to green chemistry. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. The explanation should not ignore a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to green chemistry. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 7933, 8950, 6020, 363, 263, 16372, 8368, 5007, 385, 22909, 2199, 706, 3686, 388, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 1207, 5716, 363, 920, 2551, 1033, 367, 17005, 773, 15031, 4221, 4097, 297, 8220, 304, 7933, 8950, 6020, 29889, 319, 5405, 3763, 18028, 17099, 29936, 5649, 920, 278, 7014, 