nowledge and practical judgment. In addition, consider why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to behavioral economics. A useful answer should cover what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to behavioral economics. To make the response more complete, include how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to behavioral economics. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. Please also examine the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to behavioral economics. Another important angle is the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to behavioral economics. A balanced response should mention how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to behavioral economics. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. To avoid oversimplifying, include the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to behavioral economics. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 6030, 284, 7766, 1199, 363, 263, 2319, 5381, 12271, 1602, 4821, 920, 278, 11261, 6602, 29879, 14218, 6931, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 319, 5407, 1