INFO 05-05 17:18:37 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-929d000bf2c648259efe5f8c1c8588e3-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about agriculture for a policymaker looking for practical implications rather than slogans. Please teach the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. To make the response more complete, include the short-term effects people notice first in relation to agriculture. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. Please also examine how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to agriculture. Another important angle is the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to agriculture. A balanced response should mention what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to agriculture. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. To avoid oversimplifying, include how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to agriculture. When developing the answer, connect this to a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to agriculture. A reader would also benefit from understanding the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to agriculture. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. Where appropriate, include what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to agriculture. As part of the explanation, address how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to agriculture. Also include a discussion of the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to agriculture. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. A useful answer should cover a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to agriculture. To make the response more complete, include ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to agriculture. The explanation should not ignore the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to agriculture. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. Another important angle is the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to agriculture. A balanced response should mention the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to agriculture. For practical context, discuss how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to agriculture. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. When developing the answer, connect this to how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to agriculture. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to agriculture. Please emphasize clarity, accuracy, and balanced reasoning throughout the response.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 1954, 22094, 366, 526, 10223, 292, 263, 2821, 28976, 1234, 1048, 18032, 545, 363, 263, 13665, 962, 5790, 3063, 363, 15031, 2411, 5795, 3265, 1135, 269, 1188, 550, 29889, 3529, 6860, 278, 6964, 29892, 2020, 372, 13750, 29892, 322, 920, 2305, 881, 1348, 1048, 967, 15031, 2411, 5795, 29889, 1763, 1207, 278, 2933, 901, 4866, 2989