INFO 05-05 17:19:08 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-e6579ebf475540f1820863f5ca400210-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of nutrition for a university student writing an introductory essay. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. To avoid oversimplifying, include the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to nutrition. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. A reader would also benefit from understanding the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to nutrition. The response should make room for what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to nutrition. Where appropriate, include the main causes that created the current situation in relation to nutrition. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. Also include a discussion of the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to nutrition. In addition, consider the short-term effects people notice first in relation to nutrition. A useful answer should cover how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to nutrition. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. The explanation should not ignore the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to nutrition. Please also examine the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to nutrition. Another important angle is how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to nutrition. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. For practical context, discuss how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to nutrition. To avoid oversimplifying, include how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to nutrition. When developing the answer, connect this to the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to nutrition. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. The response should make room for why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to nutrition. Where appropriate, include the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to nutrition. As part of the explanation, address which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to nutrition. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. In addition, consider how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to nutrition. A useful answer should cover what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to nutrition. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 18254, 29878, 654, 363, 263, 16372, 8368, 5007, 385, 22909, 2199, 706, 3686, 388, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 1763, 4772, 288, 874, 13699, 9215, 29892, 3160, 278, 4328, 1546, 825, 5925, 414, 1073, 322, 825, 13665, 962, 21079, 508, 2334, 297, 8220, 304, 18254, 29878, 654, 29889, 4803, 6455, 16112, 322, 5649, 2020, 1269, 1342