INFO 05-05 17:19:13 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-64c8ed8cb23f4e468ed9bd93cf8249e9-0: prompt: 'I need a well-organized answer about energy storage. Assume the reader is a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions, and focus on clarity, examples, tradeoffs, and common misunderstandings. When developing the answer, connect this to why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to energy storage. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. The response should make room for how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to energy storage. Where appropriate, include how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to energy storage. As part of the explanation, address which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to energy storage. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. In addition, consider a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to energy storage. A useful answer should cover the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to energy storage. To make the response more complete, include the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to energy storage. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. Please also examine a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to energy storage. Another important angle is the main causes that created the current situation in relation to energy storage. A balanced response should mention the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to energy storage. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. To avoid oversimplifying, include the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to energy storage. When developing the answer, connect this to the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to energy storage. A reader would also benefit from understanding the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to energy storage. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. Where appropriate, include ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to energy storage. As part of the explanation, address the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to energy storage. Also include a discussion of how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to energy storage. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. A useful answer should cover a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to energy storage. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 5864, 8635, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 1661, 771, 9202, 27886, 261, 17420, 1950, 1006, 794, 1080, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 2020, 970, 9311, 13750, 746, 2902, 1372, 23120, 1048, 278, 11261, 297, 82