INFO 05-05 17:19:18 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-c2369650da1c450d836e4b42592e1aee-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand international relations from the perspective of a city council member trying to understand tradeoffs before a vote. Please teach the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. A reader would also benefit from understanding a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to international relations. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. Where appropriate, include the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to international relations. As part of the explanation, address which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to international relations. Also include a discussion of ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to international relations. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. A useful answer should cover an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to international relations. To make the response more complete, include the most realistic solutions available today in relation to international relations. The explanation should not ignore how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to international relations. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. Another important angle is the main causes that created the current situation in relation to international relations. A balanced response should mention the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to international relations. For practical context, discuss why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to international relations. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. When developing the answer, connect this to what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to international relations. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to international relations. The response should make room for how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to international relations. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. As part of the explanation, address how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to international relations. Also include a discussion of how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to international relations. In addition, consider the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to international relations. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. To make the response more complete, include how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to international relations. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 6121, 5302, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 4272, 18701, 4509, 1811, 304, 2274, 11302, 22450, 1434, 263, 11719, 29889, 3529, 6860, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884