INFO 05-05 17:19:33 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-65ff564a78f14c0cb22f4c8d8a87230b-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of education policy for a small business owner deciding how the topic affects daily operations. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. As part of the explanation, address the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to education policy. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. In addition, consider how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to education policy. A useful answer should cover how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to education policy. To make the response more complete, include how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to education policy. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. Please also examine the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to education policy. Another important angle is a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to education policy. A balanced response should mention how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to education policy. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. To avoid oversimplifying, include how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to education policy. When developing the answer, connect this to the short-term effects people notice first in relation to education policy. A reader would also benefit from understanding how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to education policy. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. Where appropriate, include how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to education policy. As part of the explanation, address a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to education policy. Also include a discussion of how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to education policy. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. A useful answer should cover which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to education policy. To make the response more complete, include the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to education policy. The explanation should not ignore an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to education policy. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 9793, 8898, 363, 263, 2319, 5381, 12271, 1602, 4821, 920, 278, 11261, 6602, 29879, 14218, 6931, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 1094, 760, 310, 278, 8252, 29892, 3211, 278, 4328, 1546, 5557, 291, 29892, 28206, 29892, 322, 1380, 335, 362, 16650, 583, 297, 8220, 304, 9793, 8898, 29889, 19152, 278, 16225, 21104, 29892, 1871, 1230, 29892, 322, 8210, 363, 385,