INFO 05-05 17:19:38 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-eb0f3ebf98d44a539d9ee1610a5b9da5-0: prompt: 'I need a well-organized answer about genetics. Assume the reader is a policymaker looking for practical implications rather than slogans, and focus on clarity, examples, tradeoffs, and common misunderstandings. Also include a discussion of the most realistic solutions available today in relation to genetics. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. A useful answer should cover the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to genetics. To make the response more complete, include the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to genetics. The explanation should not ignore the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to genetics. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. Another important angle is how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to genetics. A balanced response should mention how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to genetics. For practical context, discuss what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to genetics. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. When developing the answer, connect this to what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to genetics. A reader would also benefit from understanding which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to genetics. The response should make room for the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to genetics. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. As part of the explanation, address the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to genetics. Also include a discussion of the main causes that created the current situation in relation to genetics. In addition, consider how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to genetics. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. To make the response more complete, include why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to genetics. The explanation should not ignore the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to genetics. Please also examine a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to genetics. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. A balanced response should mention how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to genetics. For practical context, discuss how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to genetics. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 2531, 300, 1199, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 13665, 962, 5790, 3063, 363, 15031, 2411, 5795, 3265, 1135, 269, 1188, 550, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 3115, 3160, 263, 10679, 310, 278, 1556, 1855, 4695, 6851, 3625, 982