INFO 05-05 17:19:59 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-67930463cdb24ad2b4b91865a9795119-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of history of medicine for a community organizer preparing a public workshop. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. The explanation should not ignore the main causes that created the current situation in relation to history of medicine. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. Another important angle is the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to history of medicine. A balanced response should mention the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to history of medicine. For practical context, discuss how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to history of medicine. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. When developing the answer, connect this to the most realistic solutions available today in relation to history of medicine. A reader would also benefit from understanding the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to history of medicine. The response should make room for the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to history of medicine. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. As part of the explanation, address how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to history of medicine. Also include a discussion of a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to history of medicine. In addition, consider a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to history of medicine. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. To make the response more complete, include the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to history of medicine. The explanation should not ignore the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to history of medicine. Please also examine how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to history of medicine. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. A balanced response should mention how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to history of medicine. For practical context, discuss a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to history of medicine. To avoid oversimplifying, include one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to history of medicine. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. A reader would also benefit from understanding an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to history of medicine. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 4955, 310, 26602, 363, 263, 7881, 2894, 3950, 10223, 292, 263, 970, 664, 19032, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 450, 8252, 881, 451, 11455, 278, 1667, 9946, 393, 2825, 278, 1857, 6434, 297, 8220, 304, 4955, 310, 26602, 29889, 4803, 6455, 16112, 322, 5649, 2020, 1269, 1342, 11286, 278