INFO 05-05 17:20:09 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-6137e2912b4b4942a7dd1161dd299dca-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand global trade from the perspective of a university student writing an introductory essay. Please summarize the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Another important angle is how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to global trade. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. For practical context, discuss the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to global trade. To avoid oversimplifying, include the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to global trade. When developing the answer, connect this to the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to global trade. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. The response should make room for which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to global trade. Where appropriate, include the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to global trade. As part of the explanation, address what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to global trade. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. In addition, consider an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to global trade. A useful answer should cover the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to global trade. To make the response more complete, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to global trade. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. Please also examine how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to global trade. Another important angle is the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to global trade. A balanced response should mention how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to global trade. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. To avoid oversimplifying, include the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to global trade. When developing the answer, connect this to how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to global trade. A reader would also benefit from understanding what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to global trade. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. Where appropriate, include a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to global trade. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 5534, 11302, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 16372, 8368, 5007, 385, 22909, 2199, 706, 3686, 388, 29889, 3529, 19138, 675, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 920, 2551, 1033, 367, 17005, 773, 15031, 4221, 4097, 297, 8220, 304, 5534, 11302, 29889, 8984, 714, 738, 3619, 3984, 535, 1441, 29879, 393, 1033, 3275, 304, 6460, 1602, 12112, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 278, 20813, 2305, 4049, 1207, 746, 896,