INFO 05-05 17:20:14 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-5234f586082c433b952debb49b92f0bf-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about financial literacy for a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. A balanced response should mention how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to financial literacy. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to financial literacy. When developing the answer, connect this to how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to financial literacy. A reader would also benefit from understanding which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to financial literacy. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. Where appropriate, include how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to financial literacy. As part of the explanation, address the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to financial literacy. Also include a discussion of the short-term effects people notice first in relation to financial literacy. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. A useful answer should cover what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to financial literacy. To make the response more complete, include why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to financial literacy. The explanation should not ignore the main causes that created the current situation in relation to financial literacy. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. Another important angle is what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to financial literacy. A balanced response should mention how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to financial literacy. For practical context, discuss the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to financial literacy. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. When developing the answer, connect this to how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to financial literacy. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to financial literacy. The response should make room for a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to financial literacy. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. As part of the explanation, address how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to financial literacy. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 18161, 4631, 4135, 363, 263, 1661, 771, 9202, 27886, 261, 17420, 1950, 1006, 794, 1080, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 920, 848, 11029, 50