INFO 05-05 17:20:40 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-91bd80ebfd014566850e9d5cfee46b8e-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about waste management for a policymaker looking for practical implications rather than slogans. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. The response should make room for the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to waste management. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. As part of the explanation, address a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to waste management. Also include a discussion of a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to waste management. In addition, consider the most realistic solutions available today in relation to waste management. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. To make the response more complete, include the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to waste management. The explanation should not ignore a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to waste management. Please also examine the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to waste management. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. A balanced response should mention how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to waste management. For practical context, discuss the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to waste management. To avoid oversimplifying, include the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to waste management. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to waste management. The response should make room for how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to waste management. Where appropriate, include the main causes that created the current situation in relation to waste management. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. Also include a discussion of why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to waste management. In addition, consider the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to waste management. A useful answer should cover which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to waste management. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. The explanation should not ignore how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to waste management. Please also examine how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to waste management. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 19863, 10643, 363, 263, 13665, 962, 5790, 3063, 363, 15031, 2411, 5795, 3265, 1135, 269, 1188, 550, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 166