of how data could be used responsibly in relation to robotics. In addition, consider how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to robotics. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. To make the response more complete, include what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to robotics. The explanation should not ignore an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to robotics. Please also examine ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to robotics. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. A balanced response should mention what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to robotics. For practical context, discuss the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to robotics. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 19964, 1199, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 1880, 3762, 8368, 10223, 292, 363, 263, 770, 10679, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 3115, 3160, 263, 10679, 310, 278, 11302, 22450, 1546, 6210, 29892, 6534, 2264, 29892, 21750, 3097, 29892, 322, 1472, 29899, 8489, 1411, 3097, 297, 8220, 304, 19964, 1199, 29889, 1938, 451, 2436, 263, 1423, 