INFO 05-05 17:21:15 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-cf60479f99aa40ce88b9cac7727f3a4d-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of sports science for a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. The explanation should not ignore the most realistic solutions available today in relation to sports science. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. Another important angle is an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to sports science. A balanced response should mention a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to sports science. For practical context, discuss the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to sports science. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. When developing the answer, connect this to one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to sports science. A reader would also benefit from understanding the main causes that created the current situation in relation to sports science. The response should make room for the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to sports science. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. As part of the explanation, address which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to sports science. Also include a discussion of the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to sports science. In addition, consider how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to sports science. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. To make the response more complete, include what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to sports science. The explanation should not ignore the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to sports science. Please also examine the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to sports science. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. A balanced response should mention an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to sports science. For practical context, discuss a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to sports science. To avoid oversimplifying, include what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to sports science. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. A reader would also benefit from understanding the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to sports science. The response should make room for how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to sports science. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 14717, 10466, 363, 263, 1661, 771, 9202, 27886, 261, 17420, 1950, 1006, 794, 1080, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 450, 8252, 881, 451, 11455, 278, 1556, 1855, 4695, 6851, 3625, 9826, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 4803, 263, 2821