INFO 05-05 17:21:26 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-824fbbd0915243b480fd55a94d4293ac-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand volcanology from the perspective of a journalist planning background research for an explainer article. Please analyze the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Another important angle is the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to volcanology. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. For practical context, discuss how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to volcanology. To avoid oversimplifying, include an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to volcanology. When developing the answer, connect this to a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to volcanology. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. The response should make room for how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to volcanology. Where appropriate, include the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to volcanology. As part of the explanation, address what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to volcanology. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. In addition, consider the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to volcanology. A useful answer should cover what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to volcanology. To make the response more complete, include the most realistic solutions available today in relation to volcanology. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. Please also examine how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to volcanology. Another important angle is the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to volcanology. A balanced response should mention the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to volcanology. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. To avoid oversimplifying, include what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to volcanology. When developing the answer, connect this to the main causes that created the current situation in relation to volcanology. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to volcanology. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. Where appropriate, include how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to volcanology. As part of the explanation, address how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to volcanology. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 1700, 3068, 3002, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 24452, 18987, 3239, 5925, 363, 385, 3641, 4983, 4274, 29889, 3529, 27599, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 278, 20813, 2305, 4049, 1207, 746, 896, 937, 11735, 278, 11261, 297, 8220, 304, 1700, 3068, 3002, 29889, 20355, 915, 920, 278, 11261, 4511, 29879, 304, 1432, 3250, 2834, 408, 1532, 408, 7200, 5264, 6757