education in relation to biodiversity. When developing the answer, connect this to what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to biodiversity. A reader would also benefit from understanding the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to biodiversity. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. Where appropriate, include how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to biodiversity. As part of the explanation, address the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to biodiversity. Also include a discussion of how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to biodiversity. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. A useful answer should cover how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to biodiversity. To make the response more complete, include a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to biodiversity. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 289, 2660, 24974, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 12758, 16157, 411, 694, 16905, 3239, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 385, 1342, 393, 4511, 29879, 278, 