INFO 05-05 17:21:51 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-d912496246d948f2981ff0102680fb6a-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand language learning from the perspective of a parent trying to explain the idea to a teenager. Please summarize the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to language learning. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. Where appropriate, include the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to language learning. As part of the explanation, address how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to language learning. Also include a discussion of the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to language learning. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. A useful answer should cover the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to language learning. To make the response more complete, include how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to language learning. The explanation should not ignore the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to language learning. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. Another important angle is the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to language learning. A balanced response should mention a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to language learning. For practical context, discuss how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to language learning. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. When developing the answer, connect this to a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to language learning. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to language learning. The response should make room for one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to language learning. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. As part of the explanation, address the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to language learning. Also include a discussion of a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to language learning. In addition, consider the short-term effects people notice first in relation to language learning. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 4086, 6509, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 3847, 1811, 304, 5649, 278, 2969, 304, 263, 734, 264, 1875, 29889, 3529, 19138, 675, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 920, 278, 11261, 1033, 6602, 2305, 17587, 8679, 373, 5046, 29892, 17869, 29892, 4423, 29892, 470, 9793, 297, 8220, 304, 4086, 6509, 29889, 8561, 2821, 607, 5633, 310, 278, 2228, 526, 16021, 29892, 607, 526, 17407, 29892