INFO 05-05 17:22:07 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-85b9013d2d084191b8c72fd7dd2a4675-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of democracy for a museum educator designing an accessible exhibit. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. As part of the explanation, address what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to democracy. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. In addition, consider how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to democracy. A useful answer should cover how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to democracy. To make the response more complete, include a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to democracy. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. Please also examine how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to democracy. Another important angle is how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to democracy. A balanced response should mention an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to democracy. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. To avoid oversimplifying, include one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to democracy. When developing the answer, connect this to how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to democracy. A reader would also benefit from understanding the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to democracy. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. Where appropriate, include the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to democracy. As part of the explanation, address how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to democracy. Also include a discussion of the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to democracy. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. A useful answer should cover the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to democracy. To make the response more complete, include why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to democracy. The explanation should not ignore how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to democracy. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. Another important angle is a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to democracy. A balanced response should mention what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to democracy. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 1261, 25804, 363, 263, 19133, 6320, 1061, 2874, 292, 385, 15579, 10371, 277, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 1094, 760, 310, 278, 8252, 29892, 3211, 825, 17690, 310, 21561, 526, 1556, 14040, 363, 767, 6751, 278, 2228, 297, 8220, 304, 1261, 25804, 29889, 2796, 411, 278, 1023, 470, 2211, 1556, 4100, 2125, 1450, 1036