INFO 05-05 17:22:27 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-f2b5dcea7d97488e951058cc0ccaa816-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about disaster preparedness for a journalist planning background research for an explainer article. Please analyze the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. To make the response more complete, include ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to disaster preparedness. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. Please also examine the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to disaster preparedness. Another important angle is how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to disaster preparedness. A balanced response should mention how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to disaster preparedness. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. To avoid oversimplifying, include how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to disaster preparedness. When developing the answer, connect this to what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to disaster preparedness. A reader would also benefit from understanding the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to disaster preparedness. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. Where appropriate, include the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to disaster preparedness. As part of the explanation, address what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to disaster preparedness. Also include a discussion of how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to disaster preparedness. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. A useful answer should cover the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to disaster preparedness. To make the response more complete, include one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to disaster preparedness. The explanation should not ignore an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to disaster preparedness. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. Another important angle is the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to disaster preparedness. A balanced response should mention the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to disaster preparedness. For practical context, discuss how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to disaster preparedness. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. Please emphasize clarity, accuracy, and balanced reasoning throughout the response.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 1954, 22094, 366, 526, 10223, 292, 263, 2821, 28976, 1234, 1048, 766, 1901, 13240, 2264, 363, 263, 24452, 18987, 3239, 5925, 363, 385, 3641, 4983, 4274, 29889, 3529, 27599, 278, 6964, 29892, 2020, 372, 13750, 29892, 322, 920, 2305, 881, 1348, 1048, 967, 15031, 2411, 5795, 29889, 1763, 1207, 278, 2933, 901, 4866, 29892, 3