INFO 05-05 17:22:42 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-78cd7028215b4ab696ad2e20d165ee3b-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand transportation systems from the perspective of a policymaker looking for practical implications rather than slogans. Please teach the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Another important angle is what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to transportation systems. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. For practical context, discuss how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to transportation systems. To avoid oversimplifying, include an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to transportation systems. When developing the answer, connect this to the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to transportation systems. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. The response should make room for the short-term effects people notice first in relation to transportation systems. Where appropriate, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to transportation systems. As part of the explanation, address what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to transportation systems. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. In addition, consider how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to transportation systems. A useful answer should cover the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to transportation systems. To make the response more complete, include the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to transportation systems. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. Please also examine what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to transportation systems. Another important angle is the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to transportation systems. A balanced response should mention how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to transportation systems. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. To avoid oversimplifying, include one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to transportation systems. When developing the answer, connect this to the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to transportation systems. A reader would also benefit from understanding a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to transportation systems. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. Where appropriate, include what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to transportation systems. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 8608, 362, 6757, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 13665, 962, 5790, 3063, 363, 15031, 2411, 5795, 3265, 1135, 269, 1188, 550, 29889, 3529, 6860, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 728