INFO 05-05 17:23:08 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-105fb1beba354729943b7ba1f9064ed5-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand urban planning from the perspective of a museum educator designing an accessible exhibit. Please analyze the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. A reader would also benefit from understanding how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to urban planning. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. Where appropriate, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to urban planning. As part of the explanation, address the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to urban planning. Also include a discussion of the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to urban planning. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. A useful answer should cover a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to urban planning. To make the response more complete, include what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to urban planning. The explanation should not ignore which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to urban planning. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. Another important angle is how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to urban planning. A balanced response should mention how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to urban planning. For practical context, discuss the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to urban planning. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. When developing the answer, connect this to the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to urban planning. A reader would also benefit from understanding why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to urban planning. The response should make room for what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to urban planning. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. As part of the explanation, address one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to urban planning. Also include a discussion of the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to urban planning. In addition, consider how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to urban planning. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. To make the response more complete, include an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to urban planning. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 17164, 18987, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 19133, 6320, 1061, 2874, 292, 385, 15579, 10371, 277, 29889, 3529, 27599, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 920, 10608, 2136, 414, 881, 7536, 277, 675, 8820, 746, 7788, 526, 9078, 297, 8220, 304, 17164, 18987, 29889, 1938, 451, 5251, 278, 9591, 2307, 9906, 278, 16905, 7931,