INFO 05-05 17:23:13 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-5f8118a401254c98aa511791436cbe59-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about food systems for a university student writing an introductory essay. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. The response should make room for the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to food systems. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. As part of the explanation, address the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to food systems. Also include a discussion of what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to food systems. In addition, consider the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to food systems. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. To make the response more complete, include the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to food systems. The explanation should not ignore how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to food systems. Please also examine the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to food systems. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. A balanced response should mention one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to food systems. For practical context, discuss an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to food systems. To avoid oversimplifying, include which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to food systems. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. A reader would also benefit from understanding what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to food systems. The response should make room for the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to food systems. Where appropriate, include a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to food systems. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. Also include a discussion of how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to food systems. In addition, consider why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to food systems. A useful answer should cover how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to food systems. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. The explanation should not ignore the short-term effects people notice first in relation to food systems. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 9687, 6757, 363, 263, 16372, 8368, 5007, 385, 22909, 2199, 706, 3686, 388, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 1207, 5716, 363, 278, 29380, 29892, 5264, 29892, 322, 17407, 18563, 5742, 278, 1108, 297, 8220, 304, 9687, 6757, 29889, 6652, 6202, 728, 1546, 3273, 29899, 8489, 15031, 537, 322, 147