INFO 05-05 17:23:23 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-0a31d931711344c29f6a2400078644f9-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of nutrition for a city council member trying to understand tradeoffs before a vote. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. As part of the explanation, address how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to nutrition. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. In addition, consider how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to nutrition. A useful answer should cover the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to nutrition. To make the response more complete, include the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to nutrition. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. Please also examine what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to nutrition. Another important angle is how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to nutrition. A balanced response should mention the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to nutrition. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. To avoid oversimplifying, include what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to nutrition. When developing the answer, connect this to the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to nutrition. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to nutrition. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. Where appropriate, include the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to nutrition. As part of the explanation, address the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to nutrition. Also include a discussion of the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to nutrition. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. A useful answer should cover the most realistic solutions available today in relation to nutrition. To make the response more complete, include what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to nutrition. The explanation should not ignore the short-term effects people notice first in relation to nutrition. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. Another important angle is the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to nutrition. A balanced response should mention an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to nutrition. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 18254, 29878, 654, 363, 263, 4272, 18701, 4509, 1811, 304, 2274, 11302, 22450, 1434, 263, 11719, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 1094, 760, 310, 278, 8252, 29892, 3211, 920, 304, 20820, 17924, 1136, 8841, 515, 1722, 27836, 297, 8220, 304, 18254, 29878, 654, 29889, 25589, 7