INFO 05-05 17:23:49 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-5cb1dc95c90e4c2b9819b70718964540-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of education policy for a curious adult with no technical background. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. The explanation should not ignore how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to education policy. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. Another important angle is how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to education policy. A balanced response should mention how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to education policy. For practical context, discuss how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to education policy. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. When developing the answer, connect this to how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to education policy. A reader would also benefit from understanding which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to education policy. The response should make room for the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to education policy. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. As part of the explanation, address the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to education policy. Also include a discussion of the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to education policy. In addition, consider the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to education policy. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. To make the response more complete, include the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to education policy. The explanation should not ignore one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to education policy. Please also examine a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to education policy. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. A balanced response should mention what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to education policy. For practical context, discuss how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to education policy. To avoid oversimplifying, include how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to education policy. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. A reader would also benefit from understanding ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to education policy. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 9793, 8898, 363, 263, 12758, 16157, 411, 694, 16905, 3239, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 450, 8252, 881, 451, 11455, 920, 278, 2228, 6602, 29879, 15311, 14218, 2834, 3265, 1135, 871, 2902, 1372, 297, 8220, 304, 9793, 8898, 29889, 1938, 451, 5251, 278, 9591, 2307, 9906, 278, 16905