INFO 05-05 17:23:59 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-7c369ccecc9b4216b15c49c8076260a1-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand astronomy from the perspective of a high school student preparing for a class discussion. Please break down the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Another important angle is a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to astronomy. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. For practical context, discuss how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to astronomy. To avoid oversimplifying, include the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to astronomy. When developing the answer, connect this to one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to astronomy. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. The response should make room for ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to astronomy. Where appropriate, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to astronomy. As part of the explanation, address the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to astronomy. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. In addition, consider how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to astronomy. A useful answer should cover the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to astronomy. To make the response more complete, include why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to astronomy. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. Please also examine the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to astronomy. Another important angle is the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to astronomy. A balanced response should mention the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to astronomy. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. To avoid oversimplifying, include how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to astronomy. When developing the answer, connect this to the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to astronomy. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to astronomy. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. Where appropriate, include the most realistic solutions available today in relation to astronomy. As part of the explanation, address what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to astronomy. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 20932, 29891, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 1880, 3762, 8368, 10223, 292, 363, 263, 770, 10679, 29889, 3529, 2867, 1623, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 263, 1206, 988, 1781, 7609, 1080, 508, 7738, 8062, 2582, 297, 8220, 304, 20932, 29891, 29889, 20355, 915, 920, 278, 11261, 4511, 29879, 304, 1432, 3250, 2834, 408, 1532, 408, 7