INFO 05-05 17:24:09 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-f8ccc21bf24d4042a0780a9ae3df0491-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about marine biology for a museum educator designing an accessible exhibit. Please analyze the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. For practical context, discuss how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to marine biology. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. When developing the answer, connect this to how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to marine biology. A reader would also benefit from understanding the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to marine biology. The response should make room for a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to marine biology. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. As part of the explanation, address one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to marine biology. Also include a discussion of the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to marine biology. In addition, consider the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to marine biology. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. To make the response more complete, include the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to marine biology. The explanation should not ignore how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to marine biology. Please also examine which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to marine biology. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. A balanced response should mention the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to marine biology. For practical context, discuss how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to marine biology. To avoid oversimplifying, include how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to marine biology. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. A reader would also benefit from understanding what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to marine biology. The response should make room for the most realistic solutions available today in relation to marine biology. Where appropriate, include a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to marine biology. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. Also include a discussion of the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to marine biology. In addition, consider what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to marine biology. Please emphasize clarity, accuracy, and balanced reasoning throughout the response.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 1954, 22094, 366, 526, 10223, 292, 263, 2821, 28976, 1234, 1048, 23585, 4768, 3002, 363, 263, 19133, 6320, 1061, 2874, 292, 385, 15579, 10371, 277, 29889, 3529, 27599, 278, 6964, 29892, 2020, 372, 13750, 29892, 322, 920, 2305, 881, 1348, 1048, 967, 15031, 2411, 5795, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 920, 278, 2228, 6602, 29879, 15311, 142