INFO 05-05 17:24:20 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-e903937338df4029a0dec79bc851df6a-0: prompt: 'I need a well-organized answer about climate change. Assume the reader is a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions, and focus on clarity, examples, tradeoffs, and common misunderstandings. When developing the answer, connect this to the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to climate change. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. The response should make room for what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to climate change. Where appropriate, include the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to climate change. As part of the explanation, address what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to climate change. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. In addition, consider the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to climate change. A useful answer should cover the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to climate change. To make the response more complete, include the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to climate change. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. Please also examine one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to climate change. Another important angle is an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to climate change. A balanced response should mention a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to climate change. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. To avoid oversimplifying, include how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to climate change. When developing the answer, connect this to a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to climate change. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to climate change. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. Where appropriate, include a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to climate change. As part of the explanation, address the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to climate change. Also include a discussion of how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to climate change. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. A useful answer should cover how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to climate change. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 23622, 1735, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 1661, 771, 9202, 27886, 261, 17420, 1950, 1006, 794, 1080, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 278, 11302, 22450, 1546, 6210, 29892, 6534, 2264, 29892, 21750, 3097, 29892, 322, 1472, 29899