INFO 05-05 17:24:25 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-159f336c817f4ac6b640a148bbd723a6-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand global trade from the perspective of a city council member trying to understand tradeoffs before a vote. Please teach the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. A reader would also benefit from understanding what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to global trade. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. Where appropriate, include the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to global trade. As part of the explanation, address how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to global trade. Also include a discussion of how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to global trade. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. A useful answer should cover the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to global trade. To make the response more complete, include the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to global trade. The explanation should not ignore how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to global trade. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. Another important angle is a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to global trade. A balanced response should mention the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to global trade. For practical context, discuss the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to global trade. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. When developing the answer, connect this to the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to global trade. A reader would also benefit from understanding ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to global trade. The response should make room for how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to global trade. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. As part of the explanation, address how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to global trade. Also include a discussion of an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to global trade. In addition, consider how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to global trade. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. To make the response more complete, include the short-term effects people notice first in relation to global trade. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 5534, 11302, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 4272, 18701, 4509, 1811, 304, 2274, 11302, 22450, 1434, 263, 11719, 29889, 3529, 6860, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 825, 2472, 723, 367, 1556, 4100, 297, 263, 3273, 24329, 297, 8220, 304, 5534, 11302, 29889, 8984, 714, 738, 3619, 3984, 535, 1