INFO 05-05 17:24:35 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-4083da72e11443e497e8d69f27d99339-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about supply chains for a science communicator preparing a short public talk. Please summarize the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. Where appropriate, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to supply chains. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. Also include a discussion of the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to supply chains. In addition, consider how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to supply chains. A useful answer should cover a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to supply chains. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. The explanation should not ignore how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to supply chains. Please also examine how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to supply chains. Another important angle is the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to supply chains. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. For practical context, discuss how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to supply chains. To avoid oversimplifying, include the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to supply chains. When developing the answer, connect this to the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to supply chains. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. The response should make room for ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to supply chains. Where appropriate, include the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to supply chains. As part of the explanation, address how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to supply chains. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. In addition, consider what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to supply chains. A useful answer should cover how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to supply chains. To make the response more complete, include what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to supply chains. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. Please also examine the short-term effects people notice first in relation to supply chains. Another important angle is the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to supply chains. Please emphasize clarity, accuracy, and balanced reasoning throughout the response.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 1954, 22094, 366, 526, 10223, 292, 263, 2821, 28976, 1234, 1048, 11421, 521, 2708, 363, 263, 10466, 7212, 1061, 10223, 292, 263, 3273, 970, 5193, 29889, 3529, 19138, 675, 278, 6964, 29892, 2020, 372, 13750, 29892, 322, 920, 2305, 881, 1348, 1048, 967, 15031, 2411, 5795, 29889, 6804, 8210, 29892, 3160, 263, 10230, 1546, 1023, 1422, 13501, 304, 278, 1021, 18766, 297, 8220, 304, 11421, 521, 2708, 29889, 1938, 45