INFO 05-05 17:24:55 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-5e11e75f7f904159af73ec6171e59282-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about waste management for a parent trying to explain the idea to a teenager. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. A useful answer should cover the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to waste management. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. The explanation should not ignore how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to waste management. Please also examine ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to waste management. Another important angle is which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to waste management. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. For practical context, discuss what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to waste management. To avoid oversimplifying, include the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to waste management. When developing the answer, connect this to how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to waste management. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. The response should make room for an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to waste management. Where appropriate, include the most realistic solutions available today in relation to waste management. As part of the explanation, address how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to waste management. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. In addition, consider how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to waste management. A useful answer should cover the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to waste management. To make the response more complete, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to waste management. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. Please also examine the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to waste management. Another important angle is the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to waste management. A balanced response should mention how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to waste management. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. To avoid oversimplifying, include why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to waste management. When developing the answer, connect this to the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to waste management. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 19863, 10643, 363, 263, 3847, 1811, 304, 5649, 278, 2969, 304, 263, 734, 264, 1875, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 319, 5407,