INFO 05-05 17:25:00 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-cf8a269641a64abca7005e3441bde4e8-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about ocean ecosystems for a high school student preparing for a class discussion. Please break down the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. To make the response more complete, include a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to ocean ecosystems. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. Please also examine how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to ocean ecosystems. Another important angle is the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to ocean ecosystems. A balanced response should mention how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to ocean ecosystems. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to ocean ecosystems. When developing the answer, connect this to how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to ocean ecosystems. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to ocean ecosystems. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. Where appropriate, include how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to ocean ecosystems. As part of the explanation, address the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to ocean ecosystems. Also include a discussion of how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to ocean ecosystems. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, 