connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to robotics. Another important angle is the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to robotics. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. For practical context, discuss the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to robotics. To avoid oversimplifying, include how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to robotics. When developing the answer, connect this to the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to robotics. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. The response should make room for which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to robotics. Where appropriate, include how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to robotics. As part of the explanation, address a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to robotics. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 19964, 1199, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 19133, 6320, 1061, 2874, 292, 385, 15579, 10371, 277, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 3529, 884,