INFO 05-05 17:25:16 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-f107beb012a54e62940cd9d970bf24ea-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand architecture from the perspective of a university student writing an introductory essay. Please summarize the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Another important angle is one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to architecture. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. For practical context, discuss how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to architecture. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to architecture. When developing the answer, connect this to a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to architecture. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. The response should make room for how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to architecture. Where appropriate, include an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to architecture. As part of the explanation, address the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to architecture. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. In addition, consider the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to architecture. A useful answer should cover ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to architecture. To make the response more complete, include how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to architecture. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. Please also examine which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to architecture. Another important angle is a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to architecture. A balanced response should mention the short-term effects people notice first in relation to architecture. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. To avoid oversimplifying, include a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to architecture. When developing the answer, connect this to why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to architecture. A reader would also benefit from understanding the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to architecture. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. Where appropriate, include how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to architecture. As part of the explanation, address the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to architecture. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 11258, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 16372, 8368, 5007, 385, 22909, 2199, 706, 3686, 388, 29889, 3529, 19138, 675, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 697, 18387, 1342, 393, 3732, 278, 6964, 6775, 304, 2274, 297, 8220, 304, 11258, 29889, 2796, 411, 278, 1023, 470, 2211, 1556, 4100, 