INFO 05-05 17:25:21 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-f256e4aa2f6a4b2b8abb35e437708a9e-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about earthquakes for a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. A balanced response should mention how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to earthquakes. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. To avoid oversimplifying, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to earthquakes. When developing the answer, connect this to the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to earthquakes. A reader would also benefit from understanding what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to earthquakes. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. Where appropriate, include the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to earthquakes. As part of the explanation, address how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to earthquakes. Also include a discussion of a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to earthquakes. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. A useful answer should cover the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to earthquakes. To make the response more complete, include the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to earthquakes. The explanation should not ignore a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to earthquakes. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. Another important angle is how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to earthquakes. A balanced response should mention how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to earthquakes. For practical context, discuss how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to earthquakes. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. When developing the answer, connect this to one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to earthquakes. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to earthquakes. The response should make room for how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to earthquakes. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. As part of the explanation, address the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to earthquakes. Also include a discussion of the most realistic solutions available today in relation to earthquakes. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 8437, 339, 6926, 363, 263, 1661, 771, 9202, 27886, 261, 17420, 1950, 1006, 794, 1080, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889