INFO 05-05 17:25:26 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-c2bbc3974cad446d84bd3e0aab91aa17-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about cloud computing for a city council member trying to understand tradeoffs before a vote. Please teach the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. For practical context, discuss ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to cloud computing. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. When developing the answer, connect this to the short-term effects people notice first in relation to cloud computing. A reader would also benefit from understanding the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to cloud computing. The response should make room for how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to cloud computing. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. As part of the explanation, address a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to cloud computing. Also include a discussion of the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to cloud computing. In addition, consider an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to cloud computing. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. To make the response more complete, include how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to cloud computing. The explanation should not ignore why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to cloud computing. Please also examine a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to cloud computing. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. A balanced response should mention the most realistic solutions available today in relation to cloud computing. For practical context, discuss what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to cloud computing. To avoid oversimplifying, include what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to cloud computing. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. A reader would also benefit from understanding a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to cloud computing. The response should make room for how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to cloud computing. Where appropriate, include what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to cloud computing. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. Also include a discussion of the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to cloud computing. Please emphasize clarity, accuracy, and balanced reasoning throughout the response.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 1954, 22094, 366, 526, 10223, 292, 263, 2821, 28976, 1234, 1048, 9570, 20602, 363, 263, 4272, 18701, 4509, 1811, 304, 2274, 11302, 22450, 1434, 263, 11719, 29889, 3529, 6860, 278, 6964, 29892, 2020, 372, 13750, 29892, 322, 920, 2305, 881, 1348, 1048, 967, 15031, 2411, 5795, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 11314, 936, 5155, 393, 2615, 2748, 278, 11261, 338, 7436, 297, 6944, 297, 8220, 304, 9570, 20602, 29889, 6652, 6202, 7