INFO 05-05 17:25:31 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-dd62221a52a541dd966d192647debe30-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of sports science for a journalist planning background research for an explainer article. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to sports science. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. A reader would also benefit from understanding the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to sports science. The response should make room for the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to sports science. Where appropriate, include the main causes that created the current situation in relation to sports science. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. Also include a discussion of how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to sports science. In addition, consider one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to sports science. A useful answer should cover what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to sports science. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. The explanation should not ignore a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to sports science. Please also examine the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to sports science. Another important angle is what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to sports science. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. For practical context, discuss an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to sports science. To avoid oversimplifying, include the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to sports science. When developing the answer, connect this to the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to sports science. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. The response should make room for which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to sports science. Where appropriate, include how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to sports science. As part of the explanation, address the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to sports science. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. In addition, consider a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to sports science. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 14717, 10466, 363, 263, 24452, 18987, 3239, 5925, 363, 385, 3641, 4983, 4274, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 1763, 4772, 288, 874, 13699, 9215, 29892, 3160, 920, 304, 4772, 3907, 278, 1234, 6047, 901, 3058, 1135, 278, 10757, 11286, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 8561, 278, 2933, 5407, 363, 4856, 1058, 4225, 1716, 3239, 7134