ical. To avoid oversimplifying, include the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to space exploration. When developing the answer, connect this to how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to space exploration. A reader would also benefit from understanding one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to space exploration. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. Where appropriate, include the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to space exploration. As part of the explanation, address how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to space exploration. Also include a discussion of how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to space exploration. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. A useful answer should cover how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to space exploration. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=512, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 2913, 3902, 12418, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 10466, 7212, 1061, 10223, 292, 263, 3273, 970, 5193, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 263, 1855, 29899, 11