INFO 05-05 17:25:42 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-25c16046a37c448b9dd75e41946930f8-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand behavioral economics from the perspective of a small business owner deciding how the topic affects daily operations. Please evaluate the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. To make the response more complete, include why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to behavioral economics. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. Please also examine the main causes that created the current situation in relation to behavioral economics. Another important angle is what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to behavioral economics. A balanced response should mention the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to behavioral economics. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. To avoid oversimplifying, include how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to behavioral economics. When developing the answer, connect this to how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to behavioral economics. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to behavioral economics. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. Where appropriate, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to behavioral economics. As part of the explanation, address how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to behavioral economics. Also include a discussion of the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to behavioral economics. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. A useful answer should cover the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to behavioral economics. To make the response more complete, include the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to behavioral economics. The explanation should not ignore what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to behavioral economics. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. Another important angle is how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to behavioral economics. A balanced response should mention a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to behavioral economics. For practical context, discuss how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to behavioral economics. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. When developing the answer, connect this to how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to behavioral economics. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to behavioral economics. The response should make room for the most realistic solutions available today in relation to behavioral economics. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. As part of the explanation, address the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to behavioral economics. Also include a discussion of what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to behavioral economics. In addition, consider how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to behavioral economics. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. To make the response more complete, include what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to behavioral economics. The explanation should not ignore how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to behavioral economics. Please also examine an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to behavioral economics. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. A balanced response should mention the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to behavioral economics. For practical context, discuss one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to behavioral economics. To avoid oversimplifying, include what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to behavioral economics. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. A reader would also benefit from understanding the short-term effects people notice first in relation to behavioral economics. The response should make room for a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to behavioral economics. Where appropriate, include the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to behavioral economics. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. Also include a discussion of a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to behavioral economics. In addition, consider the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to behavioral economics. A useful answer should cover the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to behavioral economics. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. The explanation should not ignore the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to behavioral e