INFO 05-05 17:25:52 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-21cab49a1f96460593a1127abb70865b-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about agriculture for a policymaker looking for practical implications rather than slogans. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. The explanation should not ignore how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to agriculture. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. Another important angle is the main causes that created the current situation in relation to agriculture. A balanced response should mention the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to agriculture. For practical context, discuss the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to agriculture. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. When developing the answer, connect this to ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to agriculture. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to agriculture. The response should make room for how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to agriculture. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. As part of the explanation, address why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to agriculture. Also include a discussion of the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to agriculture. In addition, consider a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to agriculture. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. To make the response more complete, include what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to agriculture. The explanation should not ignore the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to agriculture. Please also examine the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to agriculture. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. A balanced response should mention the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to agriculture. For practical context, discuss what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to agriculture. To avoid oversimplifying, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to agriculture. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. A reader would also benefit from understanding how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to agriculture. The response should make room for the short-term effects people notice first in relation to agriculture. Where appropriate, include what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to agriculture. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. Also include a discussion of the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to agriculture. In addition, consider how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to agriculture. A useful answer should cover how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to agriculture. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. The explanation should not ignore a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to agriculture. Please also examine how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to agriculture. Another important angle is the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to agriculture. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. For practical context, discuss how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to agriculture. To avoid oversimplifying, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to agriculture. When developing the answer, connect this to an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to agriculture. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. The response should make room for how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to agriculture. Where appropriate, include what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to agriculture. As part of the explanation, address the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to agriculture. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. In addition, consider the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to agriculture. A useful answer should cover the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to agriculture. To make the response more complete, include how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to agriculture. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. Please also examine the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to agriculture. Another important angle is how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to agriculture. A balanced response should mention a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to agriculture. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 18032, 545, 363, 263, 13665, 962, 5790, 3063, 363, 15031, 2411, 5795, 3265, 1135, 269, 1188, 550, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 450, 8252, 881, 451, 11455, 920, 278, 9545, 1163, 4822, 23507, 29892, 12786, 29892, 470, 17869, 6471, 297, 8220, 304, 18032, 545, 29889, 20355, 915, 920, 278, 11261, 4511, 29879, 304, 1432, 3250, 2834, 408, 1532, 408, 7200, 5264, 6757, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 278, 1667, 9946, 393, 2825, 278, 1857, 6434, 297, 8220, 304, 18032, 545, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 278, 16905, 11938, 393, 1207, 2560, 6851, 5189, 297, 8220, 304, 18032, 545, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 278, 4328, 1546, 825, 5925, 414, 1073, 322, 825, 13665, 962, 21079, 508, 2334, 297, 8220, 304, 18032, 545, 29889, 4803, 6455, 16112, 322, 5649, 2020, 1269, 1342, 11286, 278, 2545, 1664, 1298, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 11314, 936, 5155, 393, 2615, 2748, 278, 11261, 338, 7436, 297, 6944, 297, 8220, 304, 18032, 545, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 920, 278, 2228, 6602, 29879, 15311, 14218, 2834, 3265, 1135, 871, 2902, 1372, 297, 8220, 304, 18032, 545, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 1207, 5716, 363, 920, 304, 4772, 3907, 278, 1234, 6047, 901, 3058, 1135, 278, 10757, 11286, 297, 8220, 304, 18032, 545, 29889, 8561, 2821, 607, 5633, 310, 278, 2228, 526, 1602