ld lead to poor decisions. Another important angle is how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to urban planning. A balanced response should mention how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to urban planning. For practical context, discuss what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to urban planning. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. When developing the answer, connect this to how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to urban planning. A reader would also benefit from understanding why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to urban planning. The response should make room for which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to urban planning. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. As part of the explanation, address how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to urban planning. Also include a discussion of the most realistic solutions available today in relation to urban planning. In addition, consider how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to urban planning. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. To make the response more complete, include a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to urban planning. The explanation should not ignore which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to urban planning. Please also examine how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to urban planning. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. A balanced response should mention a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to urban planning. For practical context, discuss how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to urban planning. To avoid oversimplifying, include the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to urban planning. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. A reader would also benefit from understanding what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to urban planning. The response should make room for a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to urban planning. Where appropriate, include a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to urban planning. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. Also include a discussion of the short-term effects people notice first in relation to urban planning. In addition, consider how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to urban planning. A useful answer should cover ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to urban planning. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. The explanation should not ignore the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to urban planning. Please also examine an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to urban planning. Another important angle is an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to urban planning. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. For practical context, discuss a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to urban planning. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penal