INFO 05-05 17:27:04 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-99e40e59a0fc4444be9a186f0352cb30-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of energy storage for a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. A reader would also benefit from understanding what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to energy storage. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. Where appropriate, include an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to energy storage. As part of the explanation, address how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to energy storage. Also include a discussion of how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to energy storage. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. A useful answer should cover what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to energy storage. To make the response more complete, include how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to energy storage. The explanation should not ignore the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to energy storage. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. Another important angle is the main causes that created the current situation in relation to energy storage. A balanced response should mention the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to energy storage. For practical context, discuss what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to energy storage. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. When developing the answer, connect this to the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to energy storage. A reader would also benefit from understanding the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to energy storage. The response should make room for the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to energy storage. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. As part of the explanation, address how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to energy storage. Also include a discussion of how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to energy storage. In addition, consider one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to energy storage. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. To make the response more complete, include the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to energy storage. The explanation should not ignore how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to energy storage. Please also examine the short-term effects people notice first in relation to energy storage. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. A balanced response should mention how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to energy storage. For practical context, discuss what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to energy storage. To avoid oversimplifying, include how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to energy storage. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. A reader would also benefit from understanding why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to energy storage. The response should make room for how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to energy storage. Where appropriate, include a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to energy storage. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. Also include a discussion of which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to energy storage. In addition, consider ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to energy storage. A useful answer should cover a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to energy storage. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. The explanation should not ignore how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to energy storage. Please also examine how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to energy storage. Another important angle is what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to energy storage. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. For practical context, discuss the most realistic solutions available today in relation to energy storage. To avoid oversimplifying, include the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to energy storage. When developing the answer, connect this to the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to energy storage. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. The response should make room for how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to energy storage. Where appropriate, include the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to energy storage. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', p