INFO 05-05 17:29:30 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-7c1099fe85284fd3bdf8c3856b4a069e-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about materials science for a journalist planning background research for an explainer article. Please clarify the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. When developing the answer, connect this to the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to materials science. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. The response should make room for one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to materials science. Where appropriate, include which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to materials science. As part of the explanation, address the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to materials science. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. In addition, consider the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to materials science. A useful answer should cover how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to materials science. To make the response more complete, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to materials science. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. Please also examine how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to materials science. Another important angle is how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to materials science. A balanced response should mention why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to materials science. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. To avoid oversimplifying, include what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to materials science. When developing the answer, connect this to how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to materials science. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to materials science. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. Where appropriate, include how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to materials science. As part of the explanation, address how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to materials science. Also include a discussion of the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to materials science. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. A useful answer should cover the most realistic solutions available today in relation to materials science. To make the response more complete, include what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to materials science. The explanation should not ignore the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to materials science. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. Another important angle is the main causes that created the current situation in relation to materials science. A balanced response should mention how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to materials science. For practical context, discuss the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to materials science. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. When developing the answer, connect this to ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to materials science. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to materials science. The response should make room for how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to materials science. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. As part of the explanation, address the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to materials science. Also include a discussion of how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to materials science. In addition, consider the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to materials science. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. To make the response more complete, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to materials science. The explanation should not ignore a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to materials science. Please also examine what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to materials science. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. A balanced response should mention an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to materials science. For practical context, discuss what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to materials science. To avoid oversimplifying, include an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to materials science. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. A reader would also benefit from understanding the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to materials science. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 1954, 22094, 366, 526, 10223, 292, 263, 2821, 28976, 1234, 1048, 17279, 10466, 363, 263, 24452, 18987, 3239, 5925, 363, 385, 3641, 4983, 4274, 29889, 3529, 15544, 278, 6964, 29892, 2020, 372, 13750, 29892, 322, 920, 2305, 881, 1348, 1048, 967, 15031, 2411, 5795, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 278, 5837, 1887, 5855, 508, 1735, 825, 18139, 408, 263, 1781, 1650, 297, 8220, 304, 17279, 10466, 29889, 8561, 2821, 607, 5633, 310, 278, 2228, 526, 16021, 29892, 607, 526, 17407, 29892, 322, 607, 526, 11314, 936, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 1207, 5716, 363, 697, 18387, 1342, 393, 3732, 278, 6964, 6775, 304, 2274, 297, 8220, 304, 17279, 10466, 29889, 6804, 8210, 29892, 3160, 607, 6851, 526, 2504, 5921, 541, 1603, 9078, 491, 3438, 29892, 6287, 29892, 470, 12536, 3097, 297, 8220, 304, 17279, 10466, 29889, 1094, 760, 310, 278, 8252, 29892, 3211, 278, 3957, 1546, 5375, 19995, 322, 7200, 1788, 29899, 5563, 714, 26807, 297, 8220, 304, 17279, 10466, 29889, 19152, 278, 16225, 21104, 29892, 1871, 1230, 29892, 322, 8210, 363, 385, 21567, 10679, 29889, 512, 6124, 29892, 2050, 278, 29380, 29892, 5264, 29892, 322, 17407, 18563, 5742, 278, 1108, 297, 8220, 304, 17279, 10466, 29889, 319, 5407, 1234, 881, 4612, 920, 304, 4772, 3907, 278, 1234, 6047, 901, 3058, 1135, 278, 10757, 11286, 297, 8220, 30