INFO 05-05 17:29:51 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-63e0e19b3a3e4d3b8bbd3931db168fb4-0: prompt: 'I am trying to understand waste management from the perspective of a policymaker looking for practical implications rather than slogans. Please interpret the topic in a way that is accurate, accessible, and useful for decision making. Where appropriate, include how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to waste management. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. Also include a discussion of the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to waste management. In addition, consider how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to waste management. A useful answer should cover the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to waste management. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. The explanation should not ignore the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to waste management. Please also examine the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to waste management. Another important angle is the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to waste management. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. For practical context, discuss how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to waste management. To avoid oversimplifying, include an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to waste management. When developing the answer, connect this to how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to waste management. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. The response should make room for the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to waste management. Where appropriate, include a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to waste management. As part of the explanation, address what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to waste management. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. In addition, consider how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to waste management. A useful answer should cover the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to waste management. To make the response more complete, include the short-term effects people notice first in relation to waste management. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. Please also examine how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to waste management. Another important angle is what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to waste management. A balanced response should mention the main causes that created the current situation in relation to waste management. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. To avoid oversimplifying, include an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to waste management. When developing the answer, connect this to how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to waste management. A reader would also benefit from understanding how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to waste management. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. Where appropriate, include how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to waste management. As part of the explanation, address how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to waste management. Also include a discussion of the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to waste management. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. A useful answer should cover what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to waste management. To make the response more complete, include how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to waste management. The explanation should not ignore the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to waste management. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. Another important angle is the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to waste management. A balanced response should mention how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to waste management. For practical context, discuss what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to waste management. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. When developing the answer, connect this to the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to waste management. A reader would also benefit from understanding which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to waste management. The response should make room for a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to waste management. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. As part of the explanation, address why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to waste management. Please emphasize clarity, accuracy, and balanced reasoning throughout the response.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 626, 1811, 304, 2274, 19863, 10643, 515, 278, 18520, 310, 263, 13665, 962, 5790, 3063, 363, 15031, 2411, 5795, 3265, 1135, 269, 1188, 550, 29889, 3529, 6613, 278, 11261, 297, 263, 982, 393, 338, 16232, 29892, 15579, 29892, 322, 5407, 363, 10608, 3907, 29889, 6804, 8210, 29892, 3160, 920, 25812, 881, 367, 16459, 746, 10757, 338, 28907, 297, 8220, 304, 19863, 10643, 29889, 319, 5405, 3763, 18028, 17099, 29936, 5649, 920, 278, 7014, 29279, 304, 1269, 916, 29889, 3115, 3160, 263, 10679, 310, 278, 6297, 310, 15483, 9401, 411, 9793, 29892, 8898, 29892, 322, 6030, 1735, 297, 8220, 304, 19863, 10643, 29889, 512, 6124, 29892, 2050, 920, 304, 2198, 1716, 23633, 322, 27028, 12558, 297, 8220, 304, 19863, 10643, 29889, 319, 5407, 1234, 881, 4612, 278, 6297, 310, 1737, 5275, 29892, 22035, 12425, 29892, 322, 2130, 304, 7788, 297, 8220, 304, 19863, 10643, 29889, 4803, 263, 2821, 3829, 411, 385, 18707, 29892, 3196, 6631, 14880, 29879, 29892, 322, 263, 11473, 15997, 29889, 450, 8252, 881, 451, 11455, 278, 443, 524, 2760, 27721, 393, 508, 2615, 746, 263, 1650, 338, 6460, 368, 8688, 297, 8220, 304, 19863, 10643, 29889, 3529, 884, 25917, 278, 3957, 1546, 5375, 19995, 322, 7200, 1788, 29899, 5563, 714, 26807, 297, 8220, 304, 19863, 10643, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 278, 20813, 2305, 4049, 1207, 746, 896, 937, 11735, 278, 11261, 297, 8220, 304, 19863, 10643, 29889, 12027, 7420, 278, 4328, 1546, 19869, 29892, 3269, 362, 29892, 322, 15590,