INFO 05-05 17:30:12 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-2368e3d63a7e4e56821469d602167e3d-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of robotics for a high school student preparing for a class discussion. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. In addition, consider what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to robotics. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. To make the response more complete, include how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to robotics. The explanation should not ignore the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to robotics. Please also examine a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to robotics. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. A balanced response should mention what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to robotics. For practical context, discuss how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to robotics. To avoid oversimplifying, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to robotics. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to robotics. The response should make room for a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to robotics. Where appropriate, include an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to robotics. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. Also include a discussion of how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to robotics. In addition, consider what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to robotics. A useful answer should cover how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to robotics. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. The explanation should not ignore the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to robotics. Please also examine one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to robotics. Another important angle is the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to robotics. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. For practical context, discuss the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to robotics. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to robotics. When developing the answer, connect this to the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to robotics. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. The response should make room for how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to robotics. Where appropriate, include the most realistic solutions available today in relation to robotics. As part of the explanation, address the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to robotics. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. In addition, consider how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to robotics. A useful answer should cover the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to robotics. To make the response more complete, include the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to robotics. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. Please also examine how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to robotics. Another important angle is the main causes that created the current situation in relation to robotics. A balanced response should mention how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to robotics. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. To avoid oversimplifying, include what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to robotics. When developing the answer, connect this to the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to robotics. A reader would also benefit from understanding the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to robotics. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. Where appropriate, include which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to robotics. As part of the explanation, address how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to robotics. Also include a discussion of a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to robotics. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. A useful answer should cover a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to robotics. To make the response more complete, include how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to robotics. The explanation should not ignore which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to robotics. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=