INFO 05-05 17:30:43 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-2997cf1732724a5b894819c69e4aeb8e-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about cloud computing for a university student writing an introductory essay. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. The explanation should not ignore how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to cloud computing. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. Another important angle is how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to cloud computing. A balanced response should mention the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to cloud computing. For practical context, discuss a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to cloud computing. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. When developing the answer, connect this to which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to cloud computing. A reader would also benefit from understanding the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to cloud computing. The response should make room for the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to cloud computing. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. As part of the explanation, address a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to cloud computing. Also include a discussion of which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to cloud computing. In addition, consider how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to cloud computing. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. To make the response more complete, include ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to cloud computing. The explanation should not ignore how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to cloud computing. Please also examine a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to cloud computing. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. A balanced response should mention the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to cloud computing. For practical context, discuss the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to cloud computing. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to cloud computing. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. A reader would also benefit from understanding the main causes that created the current situation in relation to cloud computing. The response should make room for a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to cloud computing. Where appropriate, include how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to cloud computing. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. Also include a discussion of the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to cloud computing. In addition, consider the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to cloud computing. A useful answer should cover the most realistic solutions available today in relation to cloud computing. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. The explanation should not ignore what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to cloud computing. Please also examine an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to cloud computing. Another important angle is a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to cloud computing. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. For practical context, discuss what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to cloud computing. To avoid oversimplifying, include how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to cloud computing. When developing the answer, connect this to how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to cloud computing. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. The response should make room for what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to cloud computing. Where appropriate, include how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to cloud computing. As part of the explanation, address the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to cloud computing. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. In addition, consider the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to cloud computing. A useful answer should cover how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to cloud computing. To make the response more complete, include how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to cloud computing. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. Please also examine the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to cloud computing. Another important angle is the short-term effects people notice first in relation to cloud computing. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 9570, 20602, 363, 263, 16372, 8368, 5007, 385, 22909, 2199, 706, 3686, 388, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 450, 8252, 881, 451, 11455, 920, 278, 2228, 6602, 29879, 15311, 14218, 2834, 3265, 1135, 871, 2902, 1372, 297, 8220, 304, 9570, 20602, 29889, 6652, 6202, 728, 1546, 3273, 29899, 8489, 15031, 537, 322, 1472, 29899, 8489, 15075, 475, 3097, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 920, 278, 11261, 1033, 6602, 2305, 17587, 8679, 373, 5046, 29892, 17869, 29892, 4423, 29892, 470, 9793, 297, 8220, 304, 9570, 20602, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 278, 4328, 1546, 825, 5925, 414, 1073, 322, 825, 13665, 962, 21079, 508, 2334, 297, 8220, 304, 9570, 20602, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 263, 1855, 29899, 11526, 3483, 6933, 393, 947, 451, 288, 874, 13699, 1598, 278, 2228, 297, 8220, 304, 9570, 20602, 29889, 960, 2999, 1776, 9748, 1863, 29892, 2755, 278, 4549, 342, 1873, 310, 1269, 1434, 6161, 1218, 963, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 607, 4958, 881, 367, 3342, 1434, 5353, 292, 278, 4902, 297, 8220, 304, 9570, 20602, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 278, 6297, 310, 15483, 9401, 411, 9793, 29892, 8898, 29892, 322, 6030, 1735, 297, 8220, 304, 9570, 20602, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 1207, 5716, 363, 278, 11302, 22450, 1546, 6210, 29892, 6534, 2264, 29892, 21750, 3097