INFO 05-05 17:30:53 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-3a1666122c4f40b2b35698af7c542614-0: prompt: 'Imagine you are preparing a clear educational answer about sports science for a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions. Please evaluate the concept, why it matters, and how people should think about its practical implications. Please also examine an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to sports science. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. A balanced response should mention a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to sports science. For practical context, discuss which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to sports science. To avoid oversimplifying, include how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to sports science. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. A reader would also benefit from understanding which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to sports science. The response should make room for the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to sports science. Where appropriate, include the short-term effects people notice first in relation to sports science. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. Also include a discussion of a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to sports science. In addition, consider how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to sports science. A useful answer should cover how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to sports science. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. The explanation should not ignore the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to sports science. Please also examine the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to sports science. Another important angle is the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to sports science. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. For practical context, discuss the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to sports science. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to sports science. When developing the answer, connect this to a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to sports science. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. The response should make room for the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to sports science. Where appropriate, include how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to sports science. As part of the explanation, address one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to sports science. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. In addition, consider what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to sports science. A useful answer should cover how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to sports science. To make the response more complete, include the main causes that created the current situation in relation to sports science. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. Please also examine the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to sports science. Another important angle is a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to sports science. A balanced response should mention the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to sports science. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. To avoid oversimplifying, include the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to sports science. When developing the answer, connect this to how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to sports science. A reader would also benefit from understanding the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to sports science. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. Where appropriate, include how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to sports science. As part of the explanation, address the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to sports science. Also include a discussion of how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to sports science. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. A useful answer should cover the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to sports science. To make the response more complete, include ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to sports science. The explanation should not ignore how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to sports science. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. Another important angle is how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to sports science. A balanced response should mention an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to sports science. The final response should help a reader understand the issue well enough to ask better follow-up questions.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 1954, 22094, 366, 526, 10223, 292, 263, 2821, 28976, 1234, 1048, 14717, 10466, 363, 263, 1661, 771, 9202, 27886, 261, 17420, 1950, 1006, 794, 1080, 29889, 3529, 14707, 278, 6964, 29892, 2020, 372, 13750, 29892, 322, 920, 2305, 881, 1348, 1048, 967, 15031, 2411, 5795, 29889, 3529, 884, 25917, 385, 1342, 310, 263, 3619, 3984, 535, 1441, 322, 2020, 372, 338, 3984, 25369, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 319, 5405, 3763, 18028, 17099, 29936, 5649, 920, 278, 7014, 29279, 304, 1269, 916, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 263, 10230, 1546, 1023, 1422, 13501, 304, 278, 1021, 18766, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 607, 4958, 881, 367, 3342, 1434, 5353, 292, 278, 4902, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 1763, 4772, 288, 874, 13699, 9215, 29892, 3160, 920, 848, 11029, 508, 8267, 278, 12536, 3097, 310, 21204, 1080, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 341, 2509, 4100, 443, 6327, 2365, 583, 470, 27028, 1728, 3907, 278, 2933, 25160, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 607, 6851, 526, 2504, 5921, 541, 1603, 9078, 491, 3438, 29892, 6287, 29892, 470, 12536, 3097, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 1207, 5716, 363, 278, 11302, 22450, 1546, 6210, 29892, 6534, 2264, 29892, 21750, 3097, 29892, 322, 1472, 29899, 8489, 1411, 3097, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 6804, 8210, 29892, 3160, 278, 3273, 29899, 8489, 9545, 2305, 8369, 937, 297, 8220, 304, 14717, 10466, 29889, 960