INFO 05-05 17:31:14 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-42133c296cbb4f5f8e457f7762edd023-0: prompt: 'I need a well-organized answer about volcanology. Assume the reader is a journalist planning background research for an explainer article, and focus on clarity, examples, tradeoffs, and common misunderstandings. A balanced response should mention the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to volcanology. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. To avoid oversimplifying, include which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to volcanology. When developing the answer, connect this to how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to volcanology. A reader would also benefit from understanding what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to volcanology. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. Where appropriate, include how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to volcanology. As part of the explanation, address a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to volcanology. Also include a discussion of the most realistic solutions available today in relation to volcanology. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. A useful answer should cover the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to volcanology. To make the response more complete, include the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to volcanology. The explanation should not ignore the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to volcanology. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. Another important angle is how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to volcanology. A balanced response should mention which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to volcanology. For practical context, discuss how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to volcanology. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. When developing the answer, connect this to how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to volcanology. A reader would also benefit from understanding the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to volcanology. The response should make room for the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to volcanology. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. As part of the explanation, address how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to volcanology. Also include a discussion of ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to volcanology. In addition, consider what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to volcanology. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. To make the response more complete, include how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to volcanology. The explanation should not ignore the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to volcanology. Please also examine the short-term effects people notice first in relation to volcanology. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. A balanced response should mention the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to volcanology. For practical context, discuss an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to volcanology. To avoid oversimplifying, include the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to volcanology. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to volcanology. The response should make room for the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to volcanology. Where appropriate, include the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to volcanology. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. Also include a discussion of how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to volcanology. In addition, consider how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to volcanology. A useful answer should cover how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to volcanology. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. The explanation should not ignore a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to volcanology. Please also examine why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to volcanology. Another important angle is how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to volcanology. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. For practical context, discuss what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to volcanology. To avoid oversimplifying, include the main causes that created the current situation in relation to volcanology. When developing the answer, connect this to how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to volcanology. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 1700, 3068, 3002, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 24452, 18987, 3239, 5925, 363, 385, 3641, 4983, 4274, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 278, 16905, 11938, 393, 1207, 2560, 6851, 5189, 297, 8220, 304, 1700, 3068, 3002, 29889, 4803, 6455, 16112, 322, 5649, 2020, 1269, 1342, 11286, 278, 2545, 1664, 1298, 29889, 1763, 4772, 288, 874, 13699, 9215, 29892, 3160, 607, 6851, 526, 2504, 5921, 541, 1603, 9078, 491, 3438, 29892, 6287, 29892, 470, 12536, 3097, 297, 8220, 304, 1700, 3068, 3002, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 920, 278, 11261, 1795, 1106, 1422, 297, 17173, 29891, 322, 4482, 29899, 10314, 6055, 297, 8220, 304, 1700, 3068, 3002, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 825, 17690, 310, 21561, 526, 1556, 14040, 363, 767, 6751, 278, 2228, 297, 8220, 304, 1700, 3068, 3002, 29889, 6652, 6202, 728, 1546, 3273, 29899, 8489, 15031, 537, 322, 1472, 29899, 8489, 15075, 475, 3097, 29889, 6804, 8210, 29892, 3160, 920, 304, 20820, 17924, 1136, 8841, 515, 1722, 27836, 297, 8220, 304, 1700, 3068, 3002, 29889, 1094, 760, 310, 278, 8252, 29892, 3211, 263, 1206, 988, 1781, 7609, 1080, 508, 7738, 8062, 2582, 297, 8220, 304, 1700, 3068, 3002, 29889, 3115, 3160, 263, 10679, 310, 278, 1556, 1855, 4695, 6851, 3625, 9826, 297, 822