but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to data privacy. A reader would also benefit from understanding how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to data privacy. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. Where appropriate, include how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to data privacy. As part of the explanation, address what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to data privacy. Also include a discussion of the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to data privacy. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. A useful answer should cover the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to data privacy. To make the response more complete, include an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to data privacy. The explanation should not ignore which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to data privacy. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. Another important angle is the short-term effects people notice first in relation to data privacy. A balanced response should mention what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to data privacy. For practical context, discuss how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to data privacy. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. When developing the answer, connect this to how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to data privacy. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1