INFO 05-05 17:33:00 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-3497076c233445fb9edd7d1348e4c154-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about disaster preparedness for a journalist planning background research for an explainer article. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. The explanation should not ignore an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to disaster preparedness. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. Another important angle is the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to disaster preparedness. A balanced response should mention ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to disaster preparedness. For practical context, discuss how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to disaster preparedness. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. When developing the answer, connect this to one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to disaster preparedness. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to disaster preparedness. The response should make room for what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to disaster preparedness. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. As part of the explanation, address a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to disaster preparedness. Also include a discussion of the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to disaster preparedness. In addition, consider the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to disaster preparedness. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. To make the response more complete, include the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to disaster preparedness. The explanation should not ignore a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to disaster preparedness. Please also examine how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to disaster preparedness. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. A balanced response should mention how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to disaster preparedness. For practical context, discuss the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to disaster preparedness. To avoid oversimplifying, include how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to disaster preparedness. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. A reader would also benefit from understanding which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to disaster preparedness. The response should make room for how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to disaster preparedness. Where appropriate, include how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to disaster preparedness. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. Also include a discussion of the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to disaster preparedness. In addition, consider how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to disaster preparedness. A useful answer should cover a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to disaster preparedness. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. The explanation should not ignore what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to disaster preparedness. Please also examine how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to disaster preparedness. Another important angle is how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to disaster preparedness. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. For practical context, discuss the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to disaster preparedness. To avoid oversimplifying, include the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to disaster preparedness. When developing the answer, connect this to the main causes that created the current situation in relation to disaster preparedness. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. The response should make room for the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to disaster preparedness. Where appropriate, include how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to disaster preparedness. As part of the explanation, address the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to disaster preparedness. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. In addition, consider what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to disaster preparedness. A useful answer should cover the short-term effects people notice first in relation to disaster preparedness. To make the response more complete, include why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to disaster preparedness. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. Please also examine the most realistic solutions available today in relation to disaster preparedness. Another important angle is a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to disaster preparedness. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 766, 1901, 13240, 2264, 363, 263, 24452, 18987, 3239, 5925, 363, 385, 3641, 4983, 4274, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 450, 8252, 881, 451, 11455, 385, 1342, 393, 4511, 29879, 278, 11261, 304, 10466, 29892, 7766, 1199, 29892, 322, 970, 8898, 297, 8220, 304, 766, 1901, 13240, 2264, 29889, 12027, 7420, 278, 4328, 1546, 19869, 29892, 3269, 362, 29892, 322, 15590, 27262, 746, 8018, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 278, 20813, 2305, 4049, 1207, 746, 896, 937, 11735, 278, 11261, 297, 8220, 304, 766, 1901, 13240, 2264, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 11314, 936, 5155, 393, 2615, 2748, 278, 11261, 338, 7436, 297, 6944, 297, 8220, 304, 766, 1901, 13240, 2264, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 920, 278, 11261, 1033, 6602, 2305, 17587, 8679, 373, 5046, 29892, 17869, 29892, 4423, 29892, 470, 9793, 297, 8220, 304, 766, 1901, 13240, 2264, 29889, 1938, 451, 5251, 278, 9591, 2307, 9906, 278, 16905, 7931, 370, 352, 653, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 697, 18387, 1342, 393, 3732, 278, 6964, 6775, 304, 2274, 297, 8220, 304, 766, 1901, 13240, 2264, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 