INFO 05-05 17:34:44 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-975b2316a5654193884917dab6a9aebd-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about linguistics for a nonprofit volunteer comparing possible interventions. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. As part of the explanation, address how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to linguistics. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. In addition, consider how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to linguistics. A useful answer should cover the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to linguistics. To make the response more complete, include how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to linguistics. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. Please also examine the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to linguistics. Another important angle is the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to linguistics. A balanced response should mention how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to linguistics. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. To avoid oversimplifying, include the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to linguistics. When developing the answer, connect this to a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to linguistics. A reader would also benefit from understanding what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to linguistics. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. Where appropriate, include the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to linguistics. As part of the explanation, address the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to linguistics. Also include a discussion of the main causes that created the current situation in relation to linguistics. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. A useful answer should cover the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to linguistics. To make the response more complete, include the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to linguistics. The explanation should not ignore how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to linguistics. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. Another important angle is what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to linguistics. A balanced response should mention how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to linguistics. For practical context, discuss a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to linguistics. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. When developing the answer, connect this to the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to linguistics. A reader would also benefit from understanding what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to linguistics. The response should make room for how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to linguistics. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. As part of the explanation, address why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to linguistics. Also include a discussion of the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to linguistics. In addition, consider an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to linguistics. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. To make the response more complete, include the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to linguistics. The explanation should not ignore one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to linguistics. Please also examine the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to linguistics. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. A balanced response should mention how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to linguistics. For practical context, discuss how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to linguistics. To avoid oversimplifying, include how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to linguistics. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. A reader would also benefit from understanding a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to linguistics. The response should make room for how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to linguistics. Where appropriate, include what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to linguistics. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. Also include a discussion of an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to linguistics. In addition, consider the most realistic solutions available today in relation to linguistics. A useful answer should cover a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to linguistics. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 14350, 263, 2498, 29899, 28385, 5485, 8252, 1048, 21110, 6765, 363, 263, 1661, 771, 9202, 27886, 261, 17420, 1950, 1006, 794, 1080, 29889, 450, 2933, 881, 367, 1583, 29899, 1285, 7114, 322, 881, 1371, 278, 9591, 2274, 1716, 278, 6996, 2969, 322, 967, 2545, 1664, 13500, 29889, 1094, 760, 310, 278, 8252, 29892, 3211, 920, 278, 11261, 1795, 1106, 1422, 297, 17173, 29891, 322, 4482, 29899, 10314, 6055, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 6652, 6202, 728, 1546, 3273, 29899, 8489, 15031, 537, 322, 1472, 29899, 8489, 15075, 475, 3097, 29889, 512, 6124, 29892, 2050, 920, 2551, 1033, 367, 17005, 773, 15031, 4221, 4097, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 319, 5407, 1234, 881, 4612, 278, 1472, 29899, 8489, 27721, 393, 1122, 367, 22622, 304, 14111, 7389, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 1763, 1207, 278, 2933, 901, 4866, 29892, 3160, 920, 304, 1207, 278, 8252, 5407, 304, 4856, 1058, 1818, 1207, 263, 10608, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 4803, 6455, 16112, 322, 5649, 2020, 1269, 1342, 11286, 278, 2545, 1664, 1298, 29889, 3529, 884, 25917, 278, 16905, 11938, 393, 1207, 2560, 6851, 5189, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 7280, 4100, 10696, 338, 278, 443, 524, 2760, 27721, 393, 508, 2615, 746, 263, 1650, 338, 6460, 368, 8688, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 920, 2024, 19995, 16254, 411, 970, 22035, 12425, 297, 8220, 304, 21110, 6765, 29889, 12027, 7420, 825, 10757, 723, 1371, 4856, 16833, 3692, 263, 5995, 338, 4