INFO 05-05 17:34:55 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-05d2999a11c0460b9d86bfa0ba4b7b70-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of energy storage for a journalist planning background research for an explainer article. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. In addition, consider how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to energy storage. Use a clear structure with an introduction, several connected paragraphs, and a brief conclusion. To make the response more complete, include the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to energy storage. The explanation should not ignore what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to energy storage. Please also examine what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to energy storage. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. A balanced response should mention the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to energy storage. For practical context, discuss how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to energy storage. To avoid oversimplifying, include the most realistic solutions available today in relation to energy storage. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. A reader would also benefit from understanding one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to energy storage. The response should make room for an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to energy storage. Where appropriate, include how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to energy storage. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. Also include a discussion of a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to energy storage. In addition, consider a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to energy storage. A useful answer should cover the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to energy storage. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. The explanation should not ignore how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to energy storage. Please also examine the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to energy storage. Another important angle is which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to energy storage. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. For practical context, discuss which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to energy storage. To avoid oversimplifying, include the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to energy storage. When developing the answer, connect this to the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to energy storage. When there are tradeoffs, describe who benefits, who pays the cost, and why the balance is difficult. The response should make room for how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to energy storage. Where appropriate, include how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to energy storage. As part of the explanation, address the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to energy storage. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. In addition, consider how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to energy storage. A useful answer should cover how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to energy storage. To make the response more complete, include ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to energy storage. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. Please also examine a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to energy storage. Another important angle is the short-term effects people notice first in relation to energy storage. A balanced response should mention the main causes that created the current situation in relation to energy storage. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. To avoid oversimplifying, include what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to energy storage. When developing the answer, connect this to an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to energy storage. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to energy storage. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. Where appropriate, include what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to energy storage. As part of the explanation, address the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to energy storage. Also include a discussion of what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to energy storage. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. A useful answer should cover why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to energy storage. To make the response more complete, include how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to energy storage. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', p