INFO 05-05 17:35:53 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-cf7e7bb2a26449d6ae74d030e9f150b8-0: prompt: 'I need a well-organized answer about astronomy. Assume the reader is a high school student preparing for a class discussion, and focus on clarity, examples, tradeoffs, and common misunderstandings. A balanced response should mention which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to astronomy. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. To avoid oversimplifying, include the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to astronomy. When developing the answer, connect this to how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to astronomy. A reader would also benefit from understanding what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to astronomy. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. Where appropriate, include the short-term effects people notice first in relation to astronomy. As part of the explanation, address the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to astronomy. Also include a discussion of how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to astronomy. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. A useful answer should cover ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to astronomy. To make the response more complete, include the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to astronomy. The explanation should not ignore an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to astronomy. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. Another important angle is the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to astronomy. A balanced response should mention a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to astronomy. For practical context, discuss how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to astronomy. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. When developing the answer, connect this to how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to astronomy. A reader would also benefit from understanding how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to astronomy. The response should make room for how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to astronomy. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. As part of the explanation, address the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to astronomy. Also include a discussion of how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to astronomy. In addition, consider what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to astronomy. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. To make the response more complete, include the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to astronomy. The explanation should not ignore the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to astronomy. Please also examine a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to astronomy. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. A balanced response should mention how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to astronomy. For practical context, discuss the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to astronomy. To avoid oversimplifying, include how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to astronomy. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. A reader would also benefit from understanding a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to astronomy. The response should make room for why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to astronomy. Where appropriate, include which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to astronomy. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. Also include a discussion of a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to astronomy. In addition, consider the main causes that created the current situation in relation to astronomy. A useful answer should cover how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to astronomy. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. The explanation should not ignore an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to astronomy. Please also examine what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to astronomy. Another important angle is the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to astronomy. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. For practical context, discuss how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to astronomy. To avoid oversimplifying, include the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to astronomy. When developing the answer, connect this to how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to astronomy. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 306, 817, 263, 1532, 29899, 6388, 1891, 1234, 1048, 20932, 29891, 29889, 22680, 278, 9591, 338, 263, 1880, 3762, 8368, 10223, 292, 363, 263, 770, 10679, 29892, 322, 8569, 373, 7542, 537, 29892, 6455, 29892, 11302, 22450, 29892, 322, 3619, 19818, 1689, 886, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 607, 6851, 526, 2504, 5921, 541, 1603, 9078, 491, 3438, 29892, 6287, 29892, 470, 12536, 3097, 297, 8220, 304, 20932, 29891, 29889, 4803, 18387, 4086, 10940, 1950, 29892, 541, 437, 451, 28839, 13600, 29889, 1763, 4772, 288, 874, 13699, 9215, 29892, 3160, 278, 29380, 29892, 5264, 29892, 322, 17407, 18563, 5742, 278, 1108, 297, 8220, 304, 20932, 29891, 29889, 1932, 14338, 278, 1234, 29892, 4511, 445, 304, 920, 304, 2198, 1716, 23633, 322, 27028, 12558, 297, 8220, 304, 20932, 29891, 29889, 319, 9591, 723, 884, 14169, 515, 8004, 825, 5155, 263, 18109, 415, 936, 20026, 723, 3117, 2244, 297, 8220, 304, 20932, 29891, 29889, 1938, 451, 2436, 263, 1423, 1761, 29936, 7738, 263, 16165, 261, 296, 7309, 7606, 1234, 29889, 6804, 8210, 29892, 3160, 278, 3273, 29899, 8489, 9545, 2305, 8369, 937, 297, 8220, 304, 20932, 29891, 29889, 1094, 760, 310, 278, 8252, 29892, 3211, 278, 20813, 2305, 4049, 1207, 746, 896, 937, 11735, 278, 11261, 297, 8220, 304, 20932, 29891, 29889, 3115, 3160, 263, 10679, 310, 920, 278, 2228, 6602, 29879, 15311, 14218, 2834, 3265, 1135, 871, 2902, 1372, 297, 8220, 304, 20932, 29891, 29889, 4803, 6455, 16112, 322, 5649, 2020, 1269, 1342, 11286, 278, 2545, 166