dress how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to global trade. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. In addition, consider the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to global trade. A useful answer should cover the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to global trade. To make the response more complete, include the short-term effects people notice first in relation to global trade. If multiple viewpoints exist, represent the strongest version of each before evaluating them. Please also examine what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to global trade. Another important angle is the technical constraints that make simple solutions difficult in relation to global trade. A balanced response should mention how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to global trade. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. To avoid oversimplifying, include the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to global trade. When developing the answer, connect this to why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to global trade. A reader would also benefit from understanding how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to global trade. Make clear which parts of the issue are scientific, which are economic, and which are ethical. Where appropriate, include how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to global trade. As part of the explanation, address how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to global trade. The answer should be useful as background for a classroom discussion or short written report.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.