INFO 05-05 17:37:17 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-2fc27b95cec54447aeb42bb278d92bf1-0: prompt: 'Provide a thoughtful explanation of artificial intelligence for a policymaker looking for practical implications rather than slogans. The goal is not just to define the term, but to show how the topic works in real situations. In addition, consider how success could be measured using practical indicators in relation to artificial intelligence. Describe how the topic connects to everyday life as well as larger social systems. To make the response more complete, include a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to artificial intelligence. The explanation should not ignore one concrete example that makes the concept easier to understand in relation to artificial intelligence. Please also examine which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to artificial intelligence. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. A balanced response should mention what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to artificial intelligence. For practical context, discuss how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to artificial intelligence. To avoid oversimplifying, include the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to artificial intelligence. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. A reader would also benefit from understanding the main causes that created the current situation in relation to artificial intelligence. The response should make room for the most realistic solutions available today in relation to artificial intelligence. Where appropriate, include the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to artificial intelligence. Use examples from more than one context if that helps show why the issue is complicated. Also include a discussion of a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to artificial intelligence. In addition, consider a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to artificial intelligence. A useful answer should cover the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to artificial intelligence. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. The explanation should not ignore the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to artificial intelligence. Please also examine the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to artificial intelligence. Another important angle is how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to artificial intelligence. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. For practical context, discuss how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to artificial intelligence. To avoid oversimplifying, include a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to artificial intelligence. When developing the answer, connect this to the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to artificial intelligence. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. The response should make room for how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to artificial intelligence. Where appropriate, include the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to artificial intelligence. As part of the explanation, address how data quality can shape the reliability of conclusions in relation to artificial intelligence. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. In addition, consider the difference between what researchers know and what policymakers can implement in relation to artificial intelligence. A useful answer should cover how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to artificial intelligence. To make the response more complete, include how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to artificial intelligence. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. Please also examine what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to artificial intelligence. Another important angle is how to avoid making the answer sound more certain than the evidence supports in relation to artificial intelligence. A balanced response should mention the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to artificial intelligence. Explain the difference between correlation, causation, and reasonable inference when relevant. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to artificial intelligence. When developing the answer, connect this to which terms should be defined before discussing the details in relation to artificial intelligence. A reader would also benefit from understanding how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to artificial intelligence. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. Where appropriate, include an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to artificial intelligence. As part of the explanation, address the short-term effects people notice first in relation to artificial intelligence. Also include a discussion of how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to artificial intelligence. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. A useful answer should cover a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to artificial intelligence. To make the response more complete, include ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to artificial intelligence. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=-1, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=1024, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None), prompt_token_ids: [1, 9133, 680, 263, 2714, 1319, 8252, 310, 23116, 21082, 363, 263, 13665, 962, 5790, 3063, 363, 15031, 2411, 5795, 3265, 1135, 269, 1188, 550, 29889, 450, 7306, 338, 451, 925, 304, 4529, 278, 1840, 29892, 541, 304, 1510, 920, 278, 11261, 1736, 297, 1855, 18845, 29889, 512, 6124, 29892, 2050, 920, 2551, 1033, 367, 17005, 773, 15031, 4221, 4097, 297, 8220, 304, 23116, 21082, 29889, 20355, 915, 920, 278, 11261, 4511, 29879, 304, 1432, 3250, 2834, 408, 1532, 408, 7200, 5264, 6757, 29889, 1763, 1207, 278, 2933, 901, 4866, 29892, 3160, 263, 15031, 8632, 362, 310, 920, 848, 1033, 367, 1304, 5544, 14981, 297, 8220, 304, 23116, 21082, 29889, 450, 8252, 881, 451, 11455, 697, 18387, 1342, 393, 3732, 278, 6964, 6775, 304, 2274, 297, 8220, 304, 23116, 21082, 29889, 3529, 884, 25917, 607, 6851, 526, 2504, 5921, 541, 1603, 9078, 491, 3438, 29892, 6287, 29892, 470, 12536, 3097, 297, 8220, 304, 23116, 21082, 29889, 2796, 411, 278, 1023, 470, 2211, 1556, 4100, 2125, 1450, 1036, 263, 9591, 881, 6456, 29889, 319, 6411, 8362, 2933, 881, 3585, 825, 5155, 263, 18109, 415, 936, 20026, 723, 3117, 2244, 297, 8220, 304, 23116, 21082, 29889, 1152, 15031, 3030, 29892, 5353, 920, 304, 2198, 1716, 23633, 322, 27028, 12558, 297, 8220, 304, 231