ation to robotics. A balanced response should mention how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to robotics. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. To avoid oversimplifying, include how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to robotics. When developing the answer, connect this to an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to robotics. A reader would also benefit from understanding the most realistic solutions available today in relation to robotics. Explain what evidence would help someone judge whether a claim is strong or weak. Where appropriate, include ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to robotics. As part of the explanation, address how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to robotics. Also include a discussion of a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to robotics. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. A useful answer should cover how private choices interact with public infrastructure in relation to robotics. To make the response more complete, include the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to robotics. The explanation should not ignore how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to robotics. Use concrete language whenever possible, but do not sacrifice accuracy. Another important angle is the role of geography, infrastructure, and access to resources in relation to robotics. A balanced response should mention the tradeoffs between speed, fairness, affordability, and long-term durability in relation to robotics. For practical context, discuss why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to robotics. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. When developing the answer, connect this to the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to robotics. A reader would also benefit from understanding how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to robotics. The response should make room for the main causes that created the current situation in relation to robotics. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. As part of the explanation, address what kinds of institutions are most responsible for managing the issue in relation to robotics. Also include a discussion of a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to robotics. In addition, consider an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to robotics. Be explicit about any assumptions used in the explanation. To make the response more complete, include the unintended consequences that can appear when a solution is poorly designed in relation to robotics. The explanation should not ignore what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to robotics. Please also examine what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to robotics. Mention important uncertainties or limitations without making the response vague. A balanced response should mention how the topic might look different in wealthy and low-resource settings in relation to robotics. For practical context, discuss the incentives that shape how people and institutions behave in relation to robotics. To avoid oversimplifying, include the difference between prevention, adaptation, and mitigation strategies in relation to robotics. Suggest useful questions for further study at the end of the response. Avoid unsupported claims and make the reasoning easy to follow.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.