INFO 05-05 17:38:40 logger.py:37] Received request cmpl-6346388af33148efa2de2b5d237271b6-0: prompt: 'Write a general-knowledge explanation about cloud computing for a city council member trying to understand tradeoffs before a vote. The response should be self-contained and should help the reader understand both the basic idea and its broader importance. To avoid oversimplifying, include how the issue affects ordinary daily life rather than only experts in relation to cloud computing. Avoid simply listing facts; explain how the ideas relate to each other. A reader would also benefit from understanding what questions a skeptical audience would probably ask in relation to cloud computing. The response should make room for a comparison between two different approaches to the same challenge in relation to cloud computing. Where appropriate, include the most realistic solutions available today in relation to cloud computing. Do not write a checklist; produce a coherent explanatory answer. Also include a discussion of the role of technology compared with education, policy, and behavior change in relation to cloud computing. In addition, consider the risks of ignoring the issue until it becomes more expensive to address in relation to cloud computing. A useful answer should cover what a beginner is most likely to misunderstand at first in relation to cloud computing. Keep the tone neutral, informative, and appropriate for an academic discussion. The explanation should not ignore how to distinguish expert consensus from open debate in relation to cloud computing. Please also examine what information would be most important in a short presentation in relation to cloud computing. Another important angle is how uncertainty should be handled when evidence is incomplete in relation to cloud computing. Point out any common misconceptions that could lead to poor decisions. For practical context, discuss a case where good intentions can produce weak results in relation to cloud computing. To avoid oversimplifying, include the historical developments that made the issue more important over time in relation to cloud computing. When developing the answer, connect this to the assumptions people often make when they first encounter the topic in relation to cloud computing. Distinguish between short-term practicality and long-term sustainability. The response should make room for a scenario showing how the topic might matter in the next decade in relation to cloud computing. Where appropriate, include the environmental, social, and economic drivers behind the problem in relation to cloud computing. As part of the explanation, address a real-world analogy that does not oversimplify the issue in relation to cloud computing. Where useful, compare individual actions with institutional or system-level changes. In addition, consider the ways local conditions can change what counts as a good solution in relation to cloud computing. A useful answer should cover ethical questions that appear once the topic is applied in practice in relation to cloud computing. To make the response more complete, include which solutions are promising but still limited by cost, scale, or reliability in relation to cloud computing. End with the two or three most important takeaways a reader should remember. Please also examine how the topic could affect people differently depending on age, income, location, or education in relation to cloud computing. Another important angle is an example that connects the topic to science, economics, and public policy in relation to cloud computing. A balanced response should mention how to explain the topic without relying on jargon in relation to cloud computing. Use examples carefully and explain why each example supports the broader point. To avoid oversimplifying, include how decision makers should prioritize actions when resources are limited in relation to cloud computing. When developing the answer, connect this to why public trust matters when experts communicate about the topic in relation to cloud computing. A reader would also benefit from understanding the long-term consequences that may be harder to observe immediately in relation to cloud computing. Do not assume the reader already knows the technical vocabulary. Where appropriate, include how to present both benefits and limitations fairly in relation to cloud computing. As part of the explanation, address how costs and benefits may change as the solution is scaled up in relation to cloud computing. Also include a discussion of the short-term effects people notice first in relation to cloud computing. Avoid making the response depend on current news events unless the concept requires it. A useful answer should cover what an effective first step would look like for a small community in relation to cloud computing. To make the response more complete, include an example of a common misconception and why it is misleading in relation to cloud computing. The explanation should not ignore the main causes that created the current situation in relation to cloud computing. Include enough context so the answer makes sense to someone encountering the topic for the first time. Another important angle is a practical illustration of how data could be used responsibly in relation to cloud computing. A balanced response should mention how the effects differ across communities, regions, or income groups in relation to cloud computing. For practical context, discuss how to make the explanation useful to someone who must make a decision in relation to cloud computing. Make the response useful for someone who needs both background knowledge and practical judgment. When developing the answer, connect this to the connection between individual choices and larger system-level outcomes in relation to cloud computing. Please keep the answer focused on explanation rather than persuasion.', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, rep